Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tortilla trap
directions: Get out tortilla.
Slice approximately 3 slices of cheese. Place cheese slices on tortilla.
Place tortilla and cheese on a plate.
Put in microwave for 30 seconds or until cheese is melted. You can either roll up or fold in half vertically, then horizontally.

title: super energy balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine and honey in medium bowl. Stir in milk powder and raisins.
Add cereal until all pieces are evenly coated.
Drop by 1 teaspoon cereal mixture into coconut; roll into a ball.
Repeat.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix tomatoes and salt.
Let stand 12 hours.
Drain.
Heat vinegar, sugars and spices to boiling.
Pour in 4-quart saucepan. Add sliced onions to hot vinegar; mix and boil gently 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and peppers.
Bring slowly to boiling and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 9 half pints.

title: crocked swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces.
Season flour with salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Place onions in bottom of crock-pot; add meat.
Top with carrots and celery. Cover with tomato sauce.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 3 to 5 hours.

title: pineapple refresco
directions: Put everything in a blender and puree until in liquid form.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat; stir until blended. Remove from heat; gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture; pour in pie shell.
Mix coconut and pecans; sprinkle over chocolate filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool at least 4 hours before serving.

title: zucchini and yellow squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Boil until tender in water that doesn't quite cover the squash.
Boil until all the water is gone (using just a little water).
Mash squash, salt and pepper.
Brown meat with onion until done (drain).
Add to squash, bread crumbs, meat, cheese and egg.
Butter a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add a small amount of Cheddar cheese on top before baking.

title: low calorie fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: fried catfish
directions: Pour oil into a deep, large skillet.
Get it hot.
Check oil by putting a pinch of flour in the oil.
If it sizzles, it's ready. Mix flour, corn meal and salt and pepper together.
I use equal amounts.
Dip fish in mixture.
Place in hot oil.
Turn when the fish is light brown, then brown the other side.
Take out and drain on paper towel.
Eat while hot.

title: zucchini bars(like apple crisp)
directions: Simmer but do not stir zucchini and lemon juice until clear. Add nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar.
Blend well.
Set this mixture aside.

title: luscious chocolate cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake as directed on box, cool slightly. With a wooden spoon poke holes in cake.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk then the caramel topping over cake and cool completely.
When cool, top with the Cool Whip and then the crushed Heath bars.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch crosswise slices.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; dip both sides of tomato slices into mixture.
Heat shortening in a skillet until sizzling hot; put in tomatoes and cook quickly until browned on underside.
Turn tomatoes carefully; reduce heat and cook until thoroughly hot and soft through center. Remove to a hot platter and serve.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: saucy garden patch vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine soup, sour cream, milk, seasoned salt, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup French fried onions.
Spoon into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Bake in Bundt cake pan in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: betty armstrong's copper pennies
directions: Steam sliced carrots (salted) until nearly done.
Heat sauce ingredients; pour over drained carrots, pepper and onion. Marinate in refrigerator.
Keeps a long time.

title: freezer peach jam
directions: Cook peaches to soften and crush with spoon.
Add pineapple. Add sugar.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello. Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars with lids.
Let cool to room temperature and store in freezer until ready to use.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: scrumptious crab-wich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast English muffins lightly and spread with mayonnaise.
Place tomato on muffin and salt, then mound crabmeat, salt and pepper.
Top with Colby cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 1.

title: fcc barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer only for about 2 hours. Do not boil.
Add more catsup and salt if vinegar is too strong.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water with salt until tender; drain. Add tuna, cheese, onion, margarine, soup and milk.
Mix well. Place in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Add egg yolk, grated orange rind and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Knead into dough.
Form into 1 1/2-inch diameter rolls, chill 1 hour or longer.
Use dough in cookie gun, or slice and press with bottom of glass (dipped in sugar after each cookie).
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy sausage swirls
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Spread with mustard. Spread with thin layer of sausage.
Roll up and chill.
Slice each roll into 10 swirls.
Place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture into prepared skillet.
Spread cheese over this.
Add remaining mixture over cheese.
Bake as you would cornbread.
If you would like cornbread to be hot, add 1 to 2 pods of hot pepper.

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs and sugar.
Mix in butter.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Beat cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of topping.
Spread over crust.
Arrange berries in even layer.
Mix pudding with cold milk as directed on package.
Pour over berries.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, spread rest of Cool Whip and garnish with whole berries.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots, raisins, nuts and apples; pour lemon juice over and stir.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then mix sour cream and mayonnaise and mix together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli buds, discarding thick stems. Peel and chop onion. Mix broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon in bowl. Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and add to broccoli. Marinate at least 8 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, pour into dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Mix uncooked oatmeal in boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes, then add brown sugar, white sugar, oleo, eggs, flour, baking soda, cocoa and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Pour into 11 x 7-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle on top 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spiced almonds
directions: Beat egg white until foamy.
Add almonds, tossing to coat. In small bowl, combine remaining sugar and spices; toss with almonds to coat.
Spread on greased baking sheet in single layer. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool and break apart.
Cool completely and store in airtight container.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to directions on bag and drain. Saute onions, green peppers and celery.
Stir together tuna, pimentos, tomatoes, mushrooms, soup and water until blended well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and casserole is hot.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Use 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix all ingredients well (except almonds).
Place in dish and cover with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: lamb
directions: In one dish mix salt, pepper and garlic.
Make slits in the lamb and insert the garlic.
Put the meat in a roasting pan.
Rub the meat with the rest of the salt and pepper mixture.
Pour lemon juice over the meat.
Peel potatoes and cut into pieces.
Do the same as with meat (rub with salt, pepper and lemon juice).
Add the potatoes to the pan and bake at 300° for about 2 to 3 hours.
Good Luck! and Kali Oreksi!!
(have a good appetite).

title: apple crunch
directions: Place pie filling in long dish.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples, sprinkle dry cake mix over sugar mixture. Cut margarine up over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over the top of the margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave muddy animal crackers
directions: Place chocolate chips and vegetable shortening in a medium microwave-safe bowl.
Cover and microwave on High 2 minutes or until chips are melted.
Stir at 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Dip animal crackers in the chocolate mixture.
Remove with a fork. Place on waxed paper and refrigerate until cool.

title: tomato fans
directions: Rinse vegetables; pat dry.
Core tomatoes.
Slice each very thin, vertically to, but not through bottom.
Slice cucumbers thinly.
Insert cucumber slices between tomato slices.
Place tomato fans on lettuce-lined plates.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: piccalilli
directions: Mix together cabbage, tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Mix with salt and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and press to remove all liquid possible.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: With mixer on low speed, beat egg yolk in large mixer bowl until softened (about 30 seconds).
Add the sugar, egg yolk and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
With mixer on low speed, beat until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes and mash.
Measure out 2 cups mix with eggs, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 of margarine, milk, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix corn flakes, brown sugar, nuts and remaining butter. Spread over casserole and bake 10 more minutes.

title: alma's biscuits
directions: Mix together; bake in quick oven for 20 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and sugar.
Press into a well-greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: crayfish salad(yield: 4 servings)
directions: Put crayfish into a large saucepan of boiling water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer about 5 minutes, until they turn red.
Drain and rinse with cold water to cool.
Set aside about 4 crayfish for garnish.
Peel the rest, twisting off the heads and peeling away the tail shells; set aside.

title: heidi's crock-pot or slow cook chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Brush with butter; salt and pepper. Pour dry salad dressing over it.
Turn on crock-pot or slow cooker; cook for 5 to 6 hours.
Forty-five minutes before it's done, mix the cream cheese, wine, onion and soup, in a pot, over low heat; stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken; cook 30 minutes more.
Serve over wide egg noodles.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake up in pieces.
Make layers of cake in bowl and layer other ingredients as listed.
End with Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.

title: rice casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
After it is melted, add the rest of the ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: penuche
directions: Mix sugar and milk together and cook until it forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from stove and add a piece of butter the size of a walnut.
Add vanilla.
Stir in nuts and pour out on a greased platter to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes off; slice to desired size.
Let dry on paper towel.
Mix corn meal, salt, pepper and paprika in bowl or bag. Coat tomatoes in mixture.
Place coated tomatoes in hot vegetable oil and fry until golden brown.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix dry ingredients or sift together.
Add 3 cups of the flour alternately with the canned milk. Add vanilla. The other 1 cup of flour should be used on rolling surface.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
(If this browns cookies too rapidly, reduce to 325°.)
Cool and frost.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add thyme and wine.
Simmer until liquid is reduced to 1/4 cup.

title: sand cups
directions: Pour milk into large bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat with whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and half of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies in cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture. Top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Decorate.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter together.
Add noodles and drop on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: waffles
directions: I mix milk and waffle batter and flour together.
I cook it. All I know is after that you put the syrup on it and eat it.

title: cherry-cheese coffee cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and extract together until smooth.
Remove rolls from cans.
Save 4 pieces of dough and arrange the other 12 pieces on 15 inch baking stone with the long points in the center.
The pieces will hang over the edge of the baking stone.
Push the dough together to cover the stone, leaving the center open.
Fold up the center tips of dough to leave hole in the middle.
Spread cream cheese mixture over dough.
Top with pie filling.
Press perforations on saved dough and cut lengthwise into 8 strips.
Twist each strip and lay over filling like spokes on a wheel.
Fold dough over spokes around outer edge and also fold tips of dough in center.
Brush dough with beaten egg white.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer this twice in punch bowl and top with nuts.

title: green bean bake
directions: In a 5-quart microwave container, spread 2 cans of green beans.
On top of that, spread 1/3 of onion rings.
Mix Cheddar cheese soup with 3/4 cup of water and stir until smooth, then pour 1/2 of this over onion rings.
Repeat for second layer, placing last of onion rings on top.
Microwave until warm and bubbly throughout.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells 8 to 10 minutes (do not cook until completely done).
Mix cooked chicken, peas, carrots, mayonnaise, Stove Top stuffing and chopped onions.
Stuff into shells.

title: katy's crispy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crush Rice Krispies in a Ziploc plastic bag with a rolling pin.
In the meantime, melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan in the oven.
Shake each piece of chicken in bag with crushed Rice Krispies separately.
Be sure each piece is coated. Place chicken in pan.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, turning once with 15 minutes left to go.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll in nuts or bacon bits.
Chill.

title: corn spoonbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except Swiss cheese.
Pour into a 6 x 10-inch pan or casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Cut apples into a Pyrex dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Top with oatmeal and pour melted margarine over oatmeal.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: natural dog biscuits(excellent for that pampered pet!)
directions: Oil cookie sheet.
Mix dry ingredients; add oil.
Mix in egg and other ingredients.
Add water so mixture forms a ball.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. Serve with fresh fruit.
Great with strawberries, grapes, pineapple, apples, peaches and any other fruit you like.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice carrots and boil in salty water until tender.
When cool, alternate layers of carrots and thinly cut slices of pepper and onion.
Make a marinade of remaining ingredients, heating well until blended.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix together veggies, cheese, sugar and mayonnaise.
Put into Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix crackers and margarine.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread cubes in lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and milk; beat well.
Pour over bread cubes.
Set casserole in baking pan in about 1-inch hot water. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg yellows together.
Add flour, spices and milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cheese puff
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix rest, then add broccoli and cheese.
Place in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until sides are lightly browned.

title: squash or zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed.
Cook 40 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Do not overcook!
Drain well but do not rinse.
Meanwhile, in a medium-size skillet, saute garlic in butter.
Add parsley, salt and pepper, half and half and Parmesan cheese.
Stir over heat but do not boil.
Place pasta in heated bowl.
Pour sauce over pasta and serve.
Serves 4.

title: col. sanders style chicken coating
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Coat chicken in dry mixture.
Place chicken in baking dish and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
You can also use this coating for pan-frying the chicken.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion; drain off grease.
Combine browned meat with the remaining ingredients and put into a casserole.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: walnut rolls
directions: In a small bowl, combine water, yeast and the 1 teaspoon sugar.
Stir to dissolve yeast. Set aside.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add crushed pretzels. Bake in 375 degree oven for 10 minutes. Dissolve jello in boiling water, 2 cups. Stir well. Add strawberries. Put in refrigerator until almost congealed. Mix cool whip with sugar. Pile on top of baked pretzels, pour strawberries and jello mixture on top of cream cheese. Refrigerate several hours.

title: easy cobbler
directions: In casserole dish, melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: easy snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a tightly covered container.

title: transparent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix together until smooth.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake until done.
Knife inserted in filling should come out clean.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Crumble ground beef in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 can mushroom soup, diced onion, eggs, milk and salt.
Mix crackers in until desired texture for loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Remove from oven. Top with 1/2 can mushroom soup.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown the beef and onion in a skillet.
Drain.
Add the soup, water, seasonings, corn and green peppers.
Mix well and allow to simmer 15 minutes.
Then fill a greased pie dish or casserole 3/4 full, leaving room for the cornbread topping.
(Jiffy mix cornbread can be used.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix.
Put in greased dish for 45 minutes at 350°.
Grate 3/4 cup cheese.
Bake until brown.

title: best buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
In a bowl, cut Crisco into flour.
Then add buttermilk to mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on floured board. Knead lightly.
Bake 12 minutes.
This will make 6 biscuits.

title: menehune chicken
directions: Disjoint chicken wings, discard tips.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add chicken, cover and marinate 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and place in a shallow baking dish, skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn pieces and baste with marinade and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: potatoes consulate
directions: Cut slice off one-side so potato lies firm. Slice down in 1/8-inch slices to about 1/4-inch from bottom (flat side). Place in oiled baking pan. Brush with butter.

title: my grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter separately until it's soft and light.
Add sugar gradually,
creaming
together after each addition until fluffy. When sugar
and
butter
are
thoroughly blended, add eggs, cream and
lemon
rind.
Beat
until well blended.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add
to sugar mixture a little at a time.
Beat until
smooth.
Turn
dough onto floured board and roll into thin sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in a hot 400° oven for 5 minutes.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables and set aside.
Bring to a boil all other ingredients.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps good for several days.

title: honey-glazed chicken
directions: Place flour, salt and cayenne in a bowl or bag.
Add chicken pieces one at a time to coat with mixture. Pour melted oleo into 9 x 13-inch pan; place chicken in pan, turn once to coat.
Bake, uncovered, skin side up at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over chicken. Bake at 350° another 45 minutes or until tender, basting several times with pan drippings.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese barbeques
directions: Mix cheese, green pepper, onions, eggs and olives in food processor or grinder.
Add tomato soup and butter.
Mix well. Spread on 1/2 buns and put under broiler until cheese melt.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine molasses, boiling water and baking soda.
Pour over prepared shell.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until filling is set and crumbs golden brown.

title: best peach pie
directions: Fill
uncooked crust with quartered peaches, stone side up. Do	not
use
too
many
peaches.
Make mixture of sugar, butter, flour, water and egg.

title: sour milk cake
directions: In a bowl, dissolve the soda in the sour milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Mix well.
Sift in the dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add the cup of your chosen fruit; mix in.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: fake reuben sandwich
directions: Spread bread with
mustard
or
mayonnaise.
Put smoked turkey or ham on one slice of bread. Weight Watchers cheese on the other slice of bread.
Squeeze
all
of
the
juice out of kraut and put on meat.
Wrap
in foil and put in 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: matzo balls
directions: Beat yolks and whites separately.
Beat whites until almost stiff, then in fold egg yolks.

Add salt and Matzo meal. Stir until smooth. Refrigerate or set aside for about 30 minutes. Form into small balls by rolling in palms of hands (dampen palms with cold water). Drop into gently boiling clear chicken broth.
Allow to boil slowly (covered) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: yellow or zucchini squash casserole
directions: Coat 1/2 cubes in margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix squash, sour cream, soup, carrot, onion and green chilies.
Spread over cubes.
Top with remaining cubes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chocolate syrup
directions: Boil cocoa, sugar, hot water and salt for 3 minutes, then add vanilla.
Put in jar and cool.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups of syrup.
Great for chocolate milk or ice cream topping.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and Miracle Whip until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate. Serve with assorted crackers and vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Beat egg whites stiff; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg yolks. Beat together.
Add the flour mixture with milk.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Lastly, add the floured blueberries.
Place in floured and greased bread pan or muffin tins.
Sprinkle top of batter lightly with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven 35 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, except tomato sauce.
Put into loaf pan and cover with 2 strips of bacon. Pour the tomato sauce over all. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cookies
directions: You also need a mini-muffin pan.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo, brown sugar and chopped nuts until crumbly. Press into 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cool, then break into crumbs.
Put back into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Save some crumbs to sprinkle on top.

title: fruity yogurt muffins
directions: Combine rhubarb and 2 tablespoons of flour in a small bowl. Toss well and set aside.

title: 7-up cherry salad
directions: Combine water and cherry pie filling in pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from stove.
Add both packages cherry jello and stir until dissolved.
Add 1 can 7-Up very slowly.
Place in the refrigerator until jelled.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: grandma's chicken cacciatore
directions: In a 6-quart pot over medium to high, heat 1 to 2 tablespoons of oil.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove.
Saute onion 2 to 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms; continue to saute until mushrooms are golden brown and onion is soft.
Add wine and scrape pot with wooden spoon.
Add remaining ingredients; stir and cover.
Reduce heat and cook about 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in pineapple. Add flour, sifted with baking powder.
Mix well and pour in an 11 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: opal's casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in ovensafe ware.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: california carrots
directions: Cook and stir carrots and celery in butter and water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice.

title: melting moments cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make into small balls and flatten on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Cream butter and vanilla.
Add sugar, egg yolks, sour cream and baking soda.
Fold in flour, poppy seed and egg whites.
Bake at 350° for one hour in angel food cake pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Spoon into 8-inch baking dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Mix biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Pour evenly over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg with pecans in blender.
Add mixture to flour, salt and baking powder and mix well.
Roll on floured board and wrap in wax paper.
Makes 5 to 6 rolls.
Chill.

title: mini cherry cheese cake
directions: Place cupcake
liners
in
muffin
pan with one vanilla wafer in	each.
Cream
sugar
and cream cheese together.
Add eggs; blend in
lemon
juice
and vanilla.
Pour over wafer in muffin pan 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes in 375° oven. Cool; then spoon 1 teaspoon pie filling on top.

title: marshmallow pudding(without marshmallows)
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Set aside to cool while beating egg whites.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and ground beef; drain.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: abby's choco-chip cakes
directions: Preheat griddle to 375 degrees.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add chocolate chips. Mix while mixture cools. Frost cake.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Chop cherries and nuts.
Roll crackers into crumbs.
Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Combine marshmallow mixture with crumbs and cherry liquid.
Add cherries, raisins and nuts.

title: panhandle casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Layer sausage, cheeses and chilies in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix eggs, milk and flour until well blended.
Pour over layered mixture.
Decorate top with chili strips in lattice design.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over medium heat until thickened.	Pour into pie crusts; top with crust.
Cut slits in top crusts.
Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes or until crust is done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: rice chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and rice in oil until rice is soft.
Add all ingredients.
Mix in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead, frozen, thawed, then baked.

title: after dinner mints
directions: Combine egg white, cream, vanilla, oil flavoring and desired amount of coloring.
Mix well.
Add sugar, all at once, mixing thoroughly.
Add butter and additional sugar, if necessary to make mixture firm.
Shape into balls.

title: press in pie dough
directions: Mix oil and milk.
Put dry ingredients together and mix with fork, then add oil and milk mixture.
Press in a 9-inch pie plate and stick with fork.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix and bring to a boil. Boil 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat. Cool and beat until thick. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla when cool.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla in large mixing bowl. Add flour and soda.
Then mix together milk and poppy seed and add to mixture.
Add chopped walnuts, pineapple (drained) and maraschino cherries (drained).
Pour into a non-stick tube pan. Bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add bananas and walnuts; put in greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chili non carne(no salt)
directions: In large pot, saute onion and garlic in olive oil until soft. Mix in chili powder, basil, oregano and cumin.
Stir in zucchini and carrots until well blended, cooking for about 1 minute over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chopped tomatoes, undrained and drained kidney beans.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 30 to 45 minutes until thick.
Top with chopped fresh onion, tomatoes, lettuce or green peppers.

title: cake
directions: First you pout the flower in a bowl, then you pout the eggs in it and vanala, then you pout sugar milk in it than you pout it in a pot.
Then you put it in a avin then you pout sprincels then your done.

title: hamburger salami
directions: Mix well; shape into rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° on rack over pan for drainage.

title: hi-ho pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, then beat again.
Add baking powder.
Beat again for 1 minute.
Crush crackers and stir into mixture with spoon.
Stir in nuts.
Cook on 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip before serving.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in canister.
Use 1/4 to 1/3 cup mix per 1 cup beverage.
Pour boiling water over.
Stir and serve!

title: crisp toffee bars
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts; blend.
Press out firmly onto a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut bars while warm.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: mindie's stir-fried onions
directions: Cut up onions.
Cover with butter, salt, pepper and garlic. Fry until tender.
Keep turning every 2 minutes or so.
(You may need more butter; depending on preference of taste.)

title: tra-la-la
directions: You can make as little or as much as you want!
Mix equal parts.
Add brewed coffee to taste.
Top with whipped cream. Invite your friends!
Makes great gifts at Christmastime!

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Simmer onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and celery salt.
Gradually add milk and liquid from peas (1/2 cup). Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth. Combine sauce, peas and macaroni in casserole.
Put thinly sliced meat on top; bake 1/2 hour.

title: jesse stuart's cheese stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Stir in chopped parsley, coarse pepper and bottled hot sauce to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes. Drop in cheese and stir until it melts.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Mix egg, butter, milk and add to dry ingredients, blending well.
Add blueberries. Batter will be lumpy.

title: applesauce dessert waffles
directions: Toast waffles according to package directions. In a small saucepan, combine syrup, applesauce and cinnamon. Cook and stir over medium heat 3 minutes.
Place heated waffles on any dessert-style plate. Top each waffle with frozen yogurt.
Spoon warm applesauce mixture over yogurt. Serve immediately.

title: "charleston" oysters
directions: Combine bread and cracker crumbs and mix with butter.
Put a thin layer in bottom of baking dish and cover with layer of oysters.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 of cream and oyster liquor.
Repeat and cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°.
Never have more than 2 layers of oysters.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and flour. Mix well and stir in all of pineapple. Melt margarine in skillet. Add cubed bread and turn until light brown. Put on top of pineapple mixture.

title: seven course dinner
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in buttered casserole, adding salt, pepper and rice each time.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: blackberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 1 cup juice from fruit.
Add drained fruit and chill until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over jello and chill until firm.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts (9 x 13-inch pan).

title: luscious layered blueberry delight
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers, breaking where needed.
Prepare pudding as directed on package; let stand 5 minutes, then blend in whipped topping.
Spread half the pudding mixture over the crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Top with remaining pudding mixture and then remaining crackers.
Spread pie filling over top of crackers.
Chill 3 hours.
Makes 9 servings.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in large Mason jar or bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate.

title: pepperoni roll
directions: Thaw bread dough for 4 hours (don't thaw overnight, it will rise).
Flour surface.
Roll out thawed dough into a rectangle. Spread sauce over dough, overlap pepperoni on top of sauce.
Put cheese on top of pepperoni.
Roll up filled dough into a tube shape.
Fold under ends.
Pinch seams together.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake according to bread dough directions. Periodically, brush dough with milk to aid in browning.
Cool.

title: orange dip
directions: Place cream cheese and concentrate in blender or food processor; cover.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate and then serve with assorted fruit dippers.

title: mexican bean spread
directions: Blend ingredients in a food processor or blender, adding more ketchup if needed for desired consistency.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll out into small balls; drop on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: egg and ham brunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate mix for 12 hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mock reuben sandwiches
directions: Spread ham thick on bread.
Layer Swiss cheese and sauerkraut. Top with Thousand Island dressing.
Spread outside of bread with butter and grill as you would grilled cheese.

title: coney island topping for hot dogs
directions: In frypan, put oil; add meat and the spices.
Add water and cook slow about 1 hour.
Add more water if it becomes dry.

title: dutch almond cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, egg and almond flavoring, then add flour.
Make round balls with teaspoonful of dough.
Beat another egg. Take a glass and dip in raw egg and flatten balls of dough. Top with sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Place cornflakes in a large mixing bowl and set aside.
In a large saucepan combine corn syrup, brown sugar and sugar.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and peanuts; mix well.
Pour over cornflakes.
Blend. Spread evenly in a well oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over surface.
Bake 10 minutes at 250°.
Remove and smooth over top.
Cool and cut in 1-inch squares.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown the ground beef in a large pan.
While the ground beef is cooking, cut the Velveeta cheese into cubes.
After the ground beef is cooked, drain.
Put ground beef back into pan and put Velveeta cheese in with the ground beef on medium heat. add the enchilada sauce and chili.
Stir occasionally until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together; boil for 5 minutes and cool.
Add rest of ingredients; blend well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrot-zucchini bread(dietetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Gradually add Sugar Twin, beating until thick. Add flour mixture to liquid ingredients, all at once, and stir just until combined.
Stir in carrots and zucchini.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove bread from pan and cool completely.
Cut into 16 slices. Yield:
16 servings.

title: cauliflower broccoli casserole
directions: Melt Cheez Whiz along with soup in a pan. Cook vegetables until almost tender. Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put onion rings on the last 10 minutes.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, flour and pudding.
Add the oil, eggs and milk.
Beat on medium speed about 2 minutes or until well mixed.
Pour into 4 greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or tested done. Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Separate eggs, reserving egg whites for meringue.
Beat egg yolks.
Combine powdered sugar with peanut butter.
Blend until crumbly.
Spread 3/4 mixture into pie shell.
Combine sugar, salt and scalded milk together and mix well.
Pour small amount over egg yolks and mix well.
Return to mixture.
Cook in double boiler until mixture thickens.
It should look like pudding.
Add butter and vanilla. Remove from heat and pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue and sprinkle top with balance of peanut butter crumbs. Add shaved chocolate for decoration and taste.
Bake at 350° until meringue is brown.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: In a double boiler, melt morsels.
Remove from heat, add noodles and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Spoon on waxed paper and cool.
Can be frozen or sealed in airtight container.

title: powder puff cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and then nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: fruitful squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream brown sugar and butter; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture a little at a time.
Mix well.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cooled, cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: swiss meat loaf
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients with 1/4 cup tomato sauce and form into loaf.
Bake in shallow baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes. Spoon remaining tomato sauce over top, cover with cheese slices and garnish with parsley, continue baking 15 minutes.

title: saucy skillet pasta
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef with onion.
Stir in tomatoes, reserved liquid, water, loose tea, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil; stir in uncooked macaroni.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Top with cheese.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: the cleveland special fried chicken
directions: Marinate chicken pieces with garlic powder, lemon pepper and salt.
Season the flour with paprika and dip chicken into this mixture.
Fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown and crispy.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat
eggs
with fork.	Add sugar, vanilla, milk, bread and margarine.	Pour
into
greased
pan.
Bake at 400° until thick and brown, about 25 minutes.

title: hot roll-ups
directions: Mix Treet, cheese, onion and hot sauce.
Cut crust from slices of bread.
Roll bread with rolling pin and spread with meat mixture. Roll up jelly roll fashion and cut in halves or thirds. Place seam side down on a baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter and garnish with paprika.
Broil about 8 inches from heat until golden brown and cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 to 16.

title: lentil pot pie
directions: Cook vegetables in broth.
Brown flour.
Add 1 cup of hot liquid from vegetables.
Cook until thickened and combine with rest of vegetable mixture.
Add lentils, sage, parsley and salt.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: braised pork chops ala dorner
directions: In a frying pan or electric frying pan, add one teaspoon of olive oil.
Cover one side of the pork with paprika and brown (takes about 3 to 5 minutes).
While browning, put paprika on the other side and brown that also.
After both sides are brown, reduce heat to a very slow simmer and add the contents of one small can of the soup.
Do not add additional water (makes it far too dilute). Cover chops and simmer for about 30 minutes, depending on the thickness of the chops.
In a separate pot, cook the rice or noodles until they are done.
Drain and add to the pork chops about ten minutes before they are done.
This will make a rich gravy, the rice or noodles will be coated with the gravy and hopefully if you have done it right, the chops will be moist and tender.
I serve this with a green vegetable and applesauce.
Do not overcook.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix onion and hamburger.
Brown.
Add cheese.
Melt into mixture.
Add oregano, spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Stir. Put mixture on buns or English muffins.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Place under broiler for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: three-bean salad(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Let stay in refrigerator overnight. Will keep for 2 or 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Remove and put in saucepan with beef stock (or bouillon cubes with water). Add floured 1-inch cubes of round steak or beef cubes.
Add more butter if needed.
Brown quickly, then put in saucepan of beef stock.
Season to taste with salt and black pepper.
Cover tightly and cook 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add 1 package of gravy mix.
Ten minutes before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serve with or on top of wide noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: shirley clarke's no roll sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well.
Beat in egg and milk, then add dry ingredients and extract.
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Dip each ball into granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass to desired thickness. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until delicately browned.

title: potatoes chantilly
directions: Mash potatoes with butter and Carnation milk. Put in 13 x 9 glass dish. Melt slowly Old English cheese with 1 stick butter and enough Carnation to make sauce consistency. Pour sauce over potatoes. Saute fresh mushrooms in butter until tender. Spread mushrooms over potatoes and sauce. Bake in a 325° oven for about 25 minutes or until peaks turn brown.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle work surface with flour. Roll out dough. Cut in strips of desired widths. Fry in hot oil, about 1-inch, in skillet or deeper in deep fryer until golden brown on both sides.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle with awareness.
Bake in moderate oven of everyday life, using as fuel all the grudges and past unpleasantness.
Cool.
Turn out onto a platter of cheerfulness. Garnish with tears and laughter.
Serve God, country and community.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread and cut into 1 inch cubes.
Beat egg; add milk. Put bread in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam or butter.
Pour eggs and milk over bread.
Put sausage on top.
Cover with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple loaf
directions: Combine shortening and sugar in large bowl; mix well.
Add egg; blend.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn into greased, floured bread pan.
Sprinkle topping over mixture.

title: sloppy bob's
directions: Brown ground meat and drain all fat and water.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix until crumbly the flour, brown sugar, butter and oil. Reserve 1/2 cup.
Add syrup, egg, warm water and water mixed with baking soda.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans; add onion and pepper.
Mix together vinegar, salad oil, sugar and salt.
Add to bean mixture.
Toss to blend. Refrigerate for several hours.
Drain and serve.

title: campfire goulash
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, saute sausage until lightly browned on both sides.
Add onion and saute until transparent. Add potatoes and sauce mix. Gradually stir in water.
Bring to a boil and cover. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add tomatoes and green pepper. Mix well.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Dice rhubarb into unbaked pie shell.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Slowly adding whipping cream.
Pour over rhubarb. Sprinkle nutmeg over pie.
Bake 50 minutes in a 325°
oven or until set in middle.

title: spicy texas casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and add onions and green pepper. Saute.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Flake.
Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add salmon liquid, 1/3 cup crumbs, eggs, spices and salmon; mix well.
Shape into 6 cakes; roll in crumbs.
Fry in a heavy pan in about 1/8 inch of oil over moderate heat.
Brown on one side.
Turn carefully; brown on other side.
Total cooking time is 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Place on buns. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: potatoes and pennies
directions: Put potatoes, celery, onions and franks in a casserole or slow cooker.
Combine soup and milk and pour over potatoes.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
This can be made early in the day and put in a slow cooker.

title: crab stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
In skillet over medium heat, cook mushrooms in butter until all liquid is absorbed. Stir in undiluted soup, milk and wine (increase milk to 1 1/4 cups if not using wine).
Cook until sauce boils.
Reduce heat.
Add crabmeat, peas and sour cream.
Heat through; do not boil.
Toss with noodles and parsley.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Put 3 tablespoons of margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave at High until melted, 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Blend in flour, salt, mustard, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Stir in milk. Microwave on High until thickened, 4 to 6 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Line 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over edges.
Butter foil.
Set pan aside.
Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, milk and butter in prepared saucepan and bring to boil, stirring over medium-high heat.
Clip candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat to 236° soft-ball stage (about 12 minutes).
Remove saucepan from heat; remove thermometer.
Add peanut butter chips, marshmallow cream, peanuts and vanilla; stir until chips are melted.
Spread in prepared pan.
Score into square while warm.
When firm, cut fudge into squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 36.

title: rotel dip
directions: Heat cheese in slow cooker until melted.
Add tomatoes.
Keep hot to serve with tortilla chips or little Smokies.

title: mediterranean chicken with artichokes
directions: In medium bowl, combine mushrooms, onions, oil, garlic, tomato sauce
and	paste.	Add
wine,
olives, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Stir to mix ingredients.
Remove and discard skin from chicken
parts.
Place chicken in 2-quart microwave safe rectangular
dish.	Arrange chicken so that meatier areas are toward outside
of	dish (if using breasts, turn them bone side up).
Pour	tomato	mixture
over
chicken and cover dish lightly with wax
paper.
Microwave
on
High 10 minutes. Turn each piece of	chicken over.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cover with waxed paper
and	microwave
on
High
to 12 minutes. Place artichoke
hearts in baking dish, spacing among chicken. Sprinkle cheese over
all.
Cover
with
waxed
paper
and let stand 5 minutes.
If
reheating
is
necessary,
microwave on High 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: low-fat vanilla pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, combine milk, yogurt, pudding mix and vanilla. Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Spoon into serving dishes. Chill.

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: Bring slowly to boil, stirring often. Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes or until thick. Cool slightly. Measure 3 cups at a time into a blender or food processor. Cover and process on high until smooth (about 1 minute). Pour into freezer containers in serving sizes, leaving 1/4-inch headroom.
Seal, label and freeze.
Makes 16 cups.

title: sherry's ohio sheet cake
directions: Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a rolling boil. Sift together in a separate bowl the sugar, flour and salt. In large bowl, beat together eggs, buttermilk, vanilla, baking powder and baking soda. Add first and second mixture to third mixture. Mix well. Batter will be thin. Pour in cookie sheet pan (11 1/2 x 17 1/2 x 1-inch). Grease and flour if not nonstick. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with sugar, then other ingredients.
Place in graham cracker crust.
Chill before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix as given.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in 2 pans, 8 x 4-inches.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Heat chips, 1/2 syrup and butter in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in 2 cups of cereal until well coated.
Spread in pan.
Heat peanut butter, remaining syrup and the vanilla.
Remove from heat when smooth; stir in remaining cereal until well coated. Spread over mixture in pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: potatoes au gratin with sausage
directions: Slice potatoes and sausage into 1/4-inch round pieces.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Cover with thinly sliced pieces of margarine.
Place sliced sausage on top of layered potatoes.
Add sliced cheese to cover sausage. Repeat, ending with cheese as top layer.
Pour milk evenly over mixture. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: myrtle's marshmallow orange dessert
directions: Melt the marshmallows with the orange juice in a double boiler. Cool and add the whipped cream. Refrigerate in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: iowa cookies
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients; mix together and add remaining ingredients.
Place a spoonful or larger if you like on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: honey pecan barbecue sauce(from dakota's restaurant, dallas: yields 1 quart)
directions: Saute onion in	oil.
Add peppers and garlic and saute. Add remaining ingredients and cook 40 minutes and strain.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix soups, enchilada sauce, green chilies and hamburger in a bowl.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with the hamburger mixture.
Layer tortillas on top of mixture.
Layer cheese on top of this.
Layer like this, ending up with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Save 1/4 of the dough to dot the top.
Spread out remainder of dough in jelly roll pan, 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch.
Spread with Smucker's apricot preserves and sprinkle with chopped pecans, if desired.
With teaspoon, dot remaining dough on top.
Bake for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: stove top stuffing casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and put in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together stuffing mix, water and oleo.
Put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: all-night drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium size bowl, with electric mixer at high speed, beat egg white and salt until soft peaks form. Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until stiff and glossy. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto foil covered cookie sheets.
Place in oven, close door, turn oven off; do not open door.
Leave cookies in oven at least overnight.
Remove from foil; stor in airtight containers.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; mix all ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to season and chili powder for taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat
eggs
until
yolks
and
whites are blended.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add milk slowly, stirring. Pour
into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven 425° for 15
minutes, then
reduce
heat to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes longer
or
until knife inserted into center comes out clean. Makes one pie.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a jar.
Shake well.
Pour over spinach; toss gently.
Garnish with crumbled bacon and egg slices. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with damp cloth. Remove stems.
Chop and set aside.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Add 2 ounces of the Mountain Dew to the mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Roll out crescent rolls, pulling apart the sections.
(You should have 8 sections.) Using one section at a time, roll 1 quarter section of apples within the rolls.
Seal the edges together.
Place the rolled sections in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour remaining Mountain Dew over the top of the sections.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix well.
Serve 2 teaspoons per cup in hot water.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix in order given and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake about 5 minutes on bottom rack and another 5 minutes on top rack. Bake in a 350° oven.

title: double fudge brownie bar
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease bottom only of 3 x 9 inch pan.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils in large bowl overnight.
Cover with water to soak.
In large pot, saute onion, celery, and carrots in oil.
Add soaked lentils in water, tomatoes, seasonings and sugar.
Cook until lentils soften.
Add water if too thick.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put all ingredients in roaster.
Bake at 250° for 6 hours. Flake with fork.

title: french peach pie
directions: Put peaches, cut side up.
Spoon mixture over peaches and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 300° for 40 minutes.

title: old tennessee spoon bread
directions: Mix salt with cornmeal. Cut in shortening. Slowly pour in boiling water, stirring as you pour. Beat eggs in the milk to blend well and stir in. Add baking powder and blend all ingredients well. Grease casserole and pour in ingredients. bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top. Stir 2 or 3 times while baking before ingredients congeal. Serve hot from casserole. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add half and half, stirring constantly.
Add broth.
Add broccoli, nutmeg and potato soup.
Cook over low heat for 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In a food processor, grind bell and jalapeno peppers.
Rinse out processor with vinegar and add vinegar to a small saucepan along with sugar and ground peppers.
Bring to boil and boil briskly for 5 minutes.
Skim off any foam and add pectin.
Bring to boil again and boil another 1 minute.
Remove from heat; skim again if necessary, and pour into prepared jars and seal.

title: poppy cox
directions: Mix together popped corn and pecans.
Combine sugar, Karo, butter or margarine and salt in saucepan and stir until it boils. Cook syrup, stirring occasionally for 10 to 12 minutes, until it turns caramel color.
Remove from fire and add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn mix and stir until covered.
Spread on waxed paper until cool.
Break in pieces and store in a closed container.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Remove the skin from 1 whole chicken or chicken pieces (hold under warm water and pull skin off; skin removes rather easy). Place chicken or chicken pieces in pan; add enough water to cover chicken (about 5 to 6 cups).
Add celery that has been cut into 1 to 2-inch pieces (including few leaves), chopped onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add water if chicken broth decreases below desired level.
Remove chicken from broth; cool and remove from bone.
Be sure that small bones do not remain in broth (I strain the broth to be assured of removing all small bones).
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine cheese, parsley and crumbs.
Set aside.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Melt butter in medium saucepan, adding garlic to flavor.
Dip each breast in butter and roll in crumbs.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring to a boil first 3 ingredients with 2 cups water.
Steep 6 tea bags in 3 cups boiling water for 7 minutes.
Add last 3 ingredients and 2 quarts water.

title: grape wine
directions: Place ingredients in crock jar, mixing well. Cover with dish towel. Change dish towel occasionally (if mixture gets on towel). Let set in warm place for 2 weeks.
Skim off foam and stir daily. Place in bottles after mixture stops working.
After placing in smaller bottles, cover with balloons (not caps) until mixture is done working (approximately 6 to 8 weeks).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together the first 4 ingredients.
Form into a ball. Roll in nuts until covered.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 items.
Put in large baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Mix last 3 items together and sprinkle on top.
Chill at least overnight.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break up baked cake. Lay in punch bowl. Use 1/2 of crushed pineapple over crumbs, press down into cake.
Alternate layers of cherry pie filling, pudding, crushed pineapple, Cool Whip and coconut and nuts on top.
Chill.

title: seafari's savannah pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to a boil.
Add butter and slowly pour hot mixture over 3 beaten eggs.
Add pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell, which has been sprinkled with 1 Tbsp. sugar and 1 Tbsp. flour.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes or until done.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients in a medium bowl with a hand beater until smooth.
(For thinner pancakes, stir in 2 to 4 tablespoons of additional milk.)
Grease a heated pan or griddle.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat oil and eggs until fluffy.
Add berries and mix well. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and sugar and add to egg mixture, stirring until blended.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour batter into 2 greased and lightly floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix
cream
cheese,
Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Cut frozen cookies
and
overlap on pizza pan.
Bake according to package, then cool completely.
After completely cooled, then put Cool Whip mixture on and start on outside arranging fruit; put
in any order you want.
Then chill and slice.
Enjoy!
If you want, you can sprinkle coconut on top.

title: string beans in sour cream and tomato sauce
directions: Cook the green beans in lightly salted boiling water.
Don't overcook.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in a large skillet and add onions and green pepper.
Stirring occasionally, cook 5 to 8 minutes until tender but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes and basil. Boil rapidly 1 to 2 minutes until most of the juice has evaporated. Stir in the green beans.
Mix salt, sour cream, chopped egg and a few grindings of pepper.
Stir into hot vegetables and serve.

title: hot asparagus canapes
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cut slices of ham to fit bread.
Dip each asparagus spear in mayonnaise.
Fit it at one edge of bread and roll up as a jelly roll.
Fasten with a toothpick.
Place on broiler rack and toast.
Serve hot.

title: spanish green beans
directions: Cook beans in boiling salt water until tender; drain.
Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Add onions, parsley, garlic, ham and bacon; cook until ham and bacon are done.
Add wine, nutmeg and salt.
Add beans and small amount of water, if necessary.
Cover; simmer until heated through.
Coarse black pepper sprinkled on top can be added.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Chop bacon into bite size pieces.
Fry with garlic until crisp. Drain off fat and reduce heat to warm.
In the mean time, beat eggs and add cream and Parmesan.
Beat until blended.
Add egg mixture to warm bacon and slowly warm to hot.
Do not cook the eggs.
While doing this have a pot of water boiling.
Cook spaghetti until done but still firm.
Drain and put back in the hot pan.
Pour egg mixture on spaghetti and toss until the hot noodles finish cooking the eggs.
Serve immediately.
This is great with French bread and a green salad.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Serve immediately as topping.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend well after each egg.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and cook in a greased and floured pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Toss together and pour over mixed vegetables.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line pan with tortillas just lapping edges over each other.
Layer ground beef and onions.
Spread beans and 1 teaspoon salt.
Place pieces of cheese over this. Season with 1 teaspoon chili powder or garlic powder.
If desired, another layer of tortillas.
Mix soup, chilies and tomatoes in separate bowl.
Spread evenly over the top.
Bake 1 hour, turning oven to 250° last 30 minutes.

title: pecan delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar, a small amount at a time, as you continue to beat whites.
Crush the crackers and mix in with the egg whites.
Add the pecans and flavoring.
Pour into a buttered pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Put in Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: dutch ginger cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and line base of 8-inch cake pan. Cut butter into flour.
Stir in sugar and ginger.
Bind with most of the egg.
Knead dough until pliable.
Turn into pan.
Push down to smooth surface.
Pinch edge to decorate.
Using a knife, mark surface lightly in a lattice.
Glaze with remaining egg.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until firm to touch.
Cool in pan.
Serves 8.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Peel apples; put in buttered pie plate.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Cream butter, sugar, salt and egg; add flour and spread over apples.
You can add 1/2 cup walnuts if you wish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This is apple pie without crust.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Mix the above, except Fritos.
Add Fritos just before serving.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Cook celery (water to cover) until tender.
Save the liquid.
Mix all the ingredients except the noodles.
Cook about 1 hour at low temperature.
Before adding the noodles, alternate in layers in a baking dish.
Makes 6 or more servings.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese torte
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Mix the sugar and flour; mix together.
Add vanilla.
Mix the crumbs, melted butter or oleo, 1 cup sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Use rest to make crust with fingers in glass 8 x 12-inch pan.
Form crust evenly.
Spoon in egg mixture carefully. Sprinkle reserved topping on top.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together 3 times.
In a separate bowl, cream shortening and add peanut butter.
Add sugar slowly, beating thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Check for doneness.

title: baked fish florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange fish fillets in a single layer in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: christmas noel coffee braid
directions: Soften yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and eggs. Beat well.
Add flour, sifted with cinnamon and raisins.
Mix to soft dough.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into florets.
Shred cheese. Chop onion.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: apple pie in a jar
directions: Cook
until
thick and bubbly.
Add 3 tablespoons lemon juice. Peel
and slice apples into 7 jars.
Cover apples with the syrup. Process 20 minutes in water bath.

title: bake potatoes
directions: Heat coals or gas grill. Spray 18 x 13-inch piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil with cooking spray. Place potatoes on foil. Drizzle with oil; sprinkle with seasoned salt. Wrap foil securely around potatoes. Grill 4 to 5-inches from medium heat 30 minutes, turning once. Open packets; sprinkle cheese over potatoes. Cover loosely and let stand for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 6 servings.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add cocoa, sugar, flour, eggs and salt.
Stir together with spoon, not electric mixer.
Then add vanilla extract and chopped nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 9-inch dish and bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit mold
directions: Oil a 12-cup mold or Bundt pan or two 6-cup molds; set aside. In a large bowl, mix cream cheese and sour cream until fluffy. Stir in fruit cocktail, pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and walnuts.
In a medium bowl, whip whipping cream until stiff.
Fold whipped cream into fruit mixture.
Pour into prepared mold.
Cover with foil and freeze until solid.
May be frozen for several months.

title: shimmering shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar; chill until thickened.
Add 1 1/2 cups shrimp, celery, pimiento and 1 1/2 cups jello.
Spoon into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Add sour cream, parsley, onion and curry to remaining jello.
Spoon into mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold and serve with salad greens, if desired.
Garnish with remaining shrimp.

title: potato puffs
directions: Beat the egg and mashed potatoes together.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well and drop by spoonful in deep fat (hot enough to brown a cube of bread).
Fry until golden brown.

title: 9 can soup
directions: In a large pot, combine diced potatoes, onions and butter. Cook over low heat until potatoes are almost done.
Add cream soups and milk.
Simmer until blended well.
Add crabmeat and shrimp. Ready to eat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Stir in bananas.
Beat well.
Add flour and soda mixture.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Pour into a greased loaf or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Do not use an electric mixer.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and press in large baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes; cool.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package and bake 20 minutes in large greased jelly roll pan.
Then take vanilla pudding and 1 cup milk and cook until thick.
Put Saran Wrap on top and cool.
Then take margarine, Crisco and 1 cup sugar; cream well.
Add cooled pudding to creamed mixture.
Beat 10 minutes.
Spread on cooled cake. Take pineapple (juice and all), add cornstarch and 1 cup sugar, cook until thick.
Cool, then spread on top of pudding mixture. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and sour cream.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz on top.
Drizzle butter over Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle with poppy seeds.
Bake @ 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: frosted salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water; then add 7-Up.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows. Chill until set.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan and pat down.
Spread cherry pie filling on mix and sprinkle with water.
Put rest of dry mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt together the butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Pour mixture over Rice Chex.
Cool.
Put into large plastic bag containing powdered sugar.
Shake until well coated.

title: caesar salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Add dressing, croutons and cheese.
Toss and serve.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Mix in flour and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Mix all ingredients, except egg whites, then fold them in carefully.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be made the day before and refrigerated.
If you do this, take it out an hour before you want to bake it.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar into bowl.
Make a well and add eggs, salad oil, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Put into 3 small loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Keep refrigerated.

title: scrambled eggs supreme
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet; drain off all but 3 tablespoons drippings.
Combine remaining ingredients in container of electric blender.
Process on low speed until light and fluffy.
Pour into skillet with bacon and hot drippings.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until done.
Serve immediately.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: sausage-bean casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook lima beans as directed on package; drain.
Turn into ungreased 4 1/2 quart casserole.
Add baked beans and kidney beans.
In covered skillet, simmer sausages in small amount of water 5 minutes.
Drain liquid from skillet; pan fry sausages until brown on all sides.
Cut each sausage into 2 or 3 pieces; add with ham to beans.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over casserole.
Gently mix all ingredients. Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: ash-cor's caramel apples
directions: Mix together apple chunks and oranges and divide equally into 4 bowls or dessert dishes.
Prepare caramel according to package (or melt caramels on low heat).
Drizzle by spoonfuls over fruit, as much as desired.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips.
Serve immediately.
Caramel thickens as it cools and gets really gooey!

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind vegetables and squeeze out as much juice as possible. Add sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Add turmeric. Cook and bring to a boil.
Seal in jars.
Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: round steak
directions: Cut steak up into frying size pieces. Roll in flour and fry like you would fry chicken. As you take it up, place it in a pot on burner. Add more water & onions. Turn temperature down to low. Keep stirring or it will stick. Let cook until steak is tender & gravy thickens.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Generously butter a casserole dish.
Mix the soup with about 1/2 to 3/4 can of water.
Heat to almost boiling.
Add to potatoes in a casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in oven or microwave until tender.
Remove from oven and top with bacon bits, if desired.

title: speedy chicken lasagna
directions: Blend Ricotta, egg, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning and 2 tablespoons Parmesan in bowl.
Stir remaining Italian seasoning into tomato sauce.
Spread 3/4 cup of sauce in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking dish.
Place single layer of noodles over top.
Spread 1/2 of Ricotta mixture on top.
Layer lasagna noodles, 3/4 cup sauce, lasagna noodles, remaining Ricotta, lasagna noodles, 1/2 cup sauce plus cooked chicken and lasagna noodles.
Top with remaining sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Cover with foil.
If you wish, you can freeze for up to 1 month.
Thaw in refrigerator before baking.
Bake the lasagna, covered, in 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake another 10 minutes or until golden and heated through.

title: fruity orange refrigerator muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, bran cereal, sugar and baking soda, baking powder, salt, allspice and orange peel.
Add buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in fruit bits.

title: bean casserole(heart healthy)
directions: Drain beans and place in casserole.
Add spices.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh hot salsa
directions: In a large frypan or Dutch oven sweat onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of oil.
Cook until onion is translucent.
Add peppers, tomatoes and jalapeno peppers.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes. Serve hot with chips.

title: 6 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat 2 minutes after adding each egg.
Mix together the dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix all 6 flavorings; add milk.
Then add dry and liquid ingredients to cream mixture alternately.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not open oven door while cake is baking.

title: cranberry spice cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Beat together shortening and sugar at medium speed in an electric mixer about 3 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in 1 cup cranberry sauce, raisins and nuts; spoon into well-greased 9-cup Bundt pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour or until wooden pick in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan, inverting on wire rack.
Heat remaining cranberry sauce and dash of cinnamon in small saucepan. Pour warm sauce over cooled cake.
Yield:
1 (9-inch) Bundt cake.

title: sausage balls
directions: Scramble sausage in pan; slightly brown.
Pour off all grease. Add Bisquick, cheese and water.
Make in small balls.
Bake at 400° to 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Can be frozen and baked as needed.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
In an unbaked pastry shell, place 1/2 the apples.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon together. Sprinkle half of this over the apples in the pastry shell, then add remainder of apples; sprinkle the rest of the sugar and cinnamon on top of apples.

title: herb rolls
directions: Place oleo, parsley, dill, onion flakes and cheese in 9-inch pie plate.
Melt over low heat or in oven, cut biscuits in quarters.
Swish each piece in oleo mixture.
Place close together. Bake at 425 degrees (12 to 15 minutes).

title: ground beef or turkey skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground chuck or ground turkey.
Drain.
Layer noodles over meat and sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Pour tomato sauce and 2 cups water over all.
Press noodles down into liquid but do not stir.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 20 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: cheese-ham pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, then pour in unbaked pie shell.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.
Bake both pies at same time at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix together sweetened condensed milk and thawed lemonade. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 pie shells.

title: minute butterscotch pudding
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, milk and salt in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until shortening melts.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute (220°).
Remove from heat and beat until lukewarm (120°).
Stir in vanilla.
Continue beating until a smooth spreading consistency.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Place batter in 3 (5 x 9-inch) or 4 (3 x 7-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan, sprinkled with 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
While hot, take out of cake pan and flip so that walnuts are on the bottom.
Poke holes in cake with large serving fork.

title: sausage surprise
directions: Brown sausage in a Dutch oven.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Drain off drippings, reserving 1 tablespoon in Dutch oven.
Saute onions in reserved drippings 3 to 5 minutes.
Add sausage, cabbage, carrots, potatoes and water.
Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add brown sugar and regular sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in tube pan (cool 10 minutes).
Remove from pan and glaze.
