title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, bell peppers, onion, and salt; let stand one hour, then drain. Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, and celery seed; bring to a boil and cook 20 minutes; add vegetables. Boil for 1 minute; pack and seal in sterile jars. Chill before serving.

title: that meat(swiss steak)
directions: Cut up round steak.
Saute onion in oil.
Dip steak in mixture of flour, salt and pepper (and any other spices).
Brown meat in pan with onion.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Cover pan and simmer 1 hour.
(Add more water as it evaporates.)
Add Kitchen Bouquet to brown gravy.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease. Turn once.

title: chocolate covered candy
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into small balls, put on toothpick and dip.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together. Shape into a ball. Chill 2 hours.

title: chicken with cheese sauce
directions: Arrange chicken skin side up in large dish; top with one piece bacon and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Meanwhile, melt butter in saucepan and stir in flour and salt until smooth. Gradually stir in milk and cook (while stirring) until mixture thickens.
Gradually add both cheeses to the mixture and spoon over chicken.
Broil several minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: neiman-marcus squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg. Stir together until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pat mixture into bottom of well-greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat remaining 2 eggs, lightly, then beat in cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour over mixture in jelly roll pan, spreading evenly.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool pan on wire rack to room temperature.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oyster balls
directions: Mix well. Cover with foil.
Mix every once in awhile by turning the bowl upside down.
Keep in icebox overnight.

title: biscadeder's
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour and shortening until it gets crumbly.
Blend milk into flour mixture with fork.
Put sausage in mixture and continue to blend with a fork.
Add more flour if it is too sticky.
Knead it and roll it out into a flat 1/2-inch thick sheet.
Cut or roll.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 14 rolls.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, vanilla and shortening together.
Add dry ingredients and then chocolate chips.
(This batter is real stiff so if you don't have a heavy-duty mixer, you may want to use a spoon.)
Bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until coarse like meal. Add egg, cream and vanilla.
Roll on floured board.
Cut and bake about 8 minutes at 325°.

title: sara's breakfast strata
directions: Trim crust from bread. Butter slices lightly and fit into buttered 7 x 11-inch dish. Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups cheese. Top with ham. Mix eggs, onion, mustard, etc. together and pour over layered ingredients. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry pie ii
directions: Line unpricked pastry shell with double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool on a wire rack.
In a saucepan, combine the sugar, cornstarch and water until smooth.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly cooled.
Meanwhile, arrange strawberries in the crust. Pour gelatin mixture over berries.
Refrigerate until set.
Garnish with mint if desired.
Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: plain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then stir in flour.
Mix 2 minutes at low speed.
Add milk and flavoring.
Beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: taco soup
directions: Simmer ingredients for 1 to 2 hours.
Top with shredded cheese, Fritos and sour cream when serving.

title: waldorf astoria cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating well.
Sift all the dry ingredients but soda and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Then combine vinegar and soda and stir into the creamed mixture.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) well-greased cake pans or 3 (8-inch) cake pans at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and water together.
Add all the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil; stirring constantly.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve over cream cheese or use as a relish for ham/pork.
Makes 3 cups.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add 1 pound (2 cups) crab meat (back fin best).
Best if made at least 2 hours before cooking.

title: never fail rare roast beef
directions: Place onion on roast with toothpicks.
Pour Worcestershire sauce over roast.
Season with spices.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Cover roast with aluminum foil.
When oven is ready, place roast in oven and cook 5 minutes per pound. Turn off oven and leave door closed for 2 hours. Don't peek!

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Mix all together and heat in crock-pot for 4 hours or greater.

title: peach pudding
directions: Place peach halves in buttered custard cups or 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar, blend in cinnamon and breadcrumbs.
Stir in melted margarine.
Spread over peaches and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine in large bowl; cook on High in microwave for 2 minutes.
(Cover with Saran Wrap.)
Blend in with mixer vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a greased square pan.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before cutting.
Once cut into squares, I store it in the refrigerator.

title: "idiots delight" bars
directions: Mix and pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan the first 5 ingredients.
Bake 12 minutes at 375° or longer for crispness. Set aside to cool.
Melt chocolate chips and blend in peanut butter.
Spread over crust; refrigerate to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook all together; seal in sterilized jars.

title: herb-bran muffins
directions: Stir together the flours, baking powder, salt, sugar, sesame seed, dry mustard and herb of choice.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the bran cereal and the milk.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add the egg and butter or margarine, blending well.
Add the flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Coat a 12-muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray or line with muffin cups.
Fill each 2/3 full with muffin mixture.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean.

title: corned beef and cabbage(the easy way)
directions: Mix soup and mustard.
Break corned beef into bite-size. Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Spread	beans
in
a large plate.
Peel and mash avocado(s). Spread
over beans.
Add taco seasoning to sour cream. Put	over avocado(s).
Sprinkle
cheese over sour cream, then black
olives. Put
sauce
in middle of dish inside half of a cleaned out green pepper.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to directions.
Immediately after taking cake from the oven, use a fork to poke holes in the cake.
Pour the can of sweetened condensed milk over the hot cake. Next, pour a jar of hot fudge topping over the cake.
Cool cake in refrigerator. Before serving, top with chocolate Dream Whip.

title: lima hamburger skillet
directions: Dice onion; slice celery and fry both in oil until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add hamburger; cook and stir until meat is browned. Stir in tomatoes, catsup, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and lima beans.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat about 15 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine egg, milk, shortening and add to dry ingredients. Stir until moist.
Cook on greased griddle.

title: iced tea devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add
eggs,
one at a time. Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add alternately with iced tea and soda. Add vanilla.
Bake about 50 minutes (or until toothpick inserted into center comes
clean)
at
325° in a Pyrex baking dish (8 x 11 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch) or 350° in metal pan.
It takes a little longer to bake in glass pan.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine above ingredients and put in an ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 25 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, vanilla and butter until smooth.
Add chocolate chips and brown sugar; pour in ungreased deep dish baker.
Sprinkle in the remaining 1/4 cup unsweetened cocoa.
Place the ingredients on oven rack, then add boiling water.
Bake for 35 minutes; cool for 10.
Serve over ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: sand bakkels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, placing one rack on top of oven and one rack on lower shelf in oven.
In bowl, cream together sugar, butter and margarine. Add egg yolk, vanilla and half and half. Add dry ingredients, starting with flour.
Mix well.
Press dough into sand bakkel tins.
Bake, placing on lower shelf, for 7 minutes, then top shelf for 2 minutes (9 minutes total).
Slide off sheet.
Leave them right side up until cool enough to handle. Pop out of tin with a slightly squeeze.
Makes about 45 bakkels.

title: easy cheese eggs ala king
directions: In a saucepan, cover and cook celery, green pepper and onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir in celery soup, cheese and milk; heat and stir until cheese melts. Gently stir in sliced eggs and pimiento.
Serve spooned over buttered toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla, then the dry ingredients and nuts.
Form in long rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and let stand overnight.
I usually put them in the freezer until you can slice them off nicely.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for about 10 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Makes quite a lot of cookies.

title: pizza twists
directions: Separate the breadsticks.
Stick the ends together so each one forms a circle and then twist it into a figure 8.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and Italian seasoning.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown meat and mix with all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spice strips
directions: Mix all ingredients together in the order given.
Chill dough. Remove from refrigerator and divide dough into 6 parts.
Roll each part in sugar until 10-inches long and 3/4-inch wide.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place 2 rolls on each of 3 foil lined cookie sheets.
Sprinkle rolls with sugar.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour. Slice on diagonal while still warm.
Allow to cool thoroughly on cookie sheet.
May be frozen.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-inch muffin tin.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; add alternately with milk.
Do not overmix.
Fold in nuts and raisins.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Combine chili sauce and grape jelly in large sauce pan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 3 minutes or until mixture begins to boil.
Add sausage; cook an additional 3 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring often.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage at room temperature.
Combine all; mix well. Roll into bite-size balls.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 100 balls.

title: potatoes on the grill
directions: Using heavy duty aluminum foil, use a 12-inch square.
Place on the foil the potato, onion, grease and salt and pepper.
Fold edges, overlapping tightly.
Place on grill.
Turn occasionally. Check for doneness after 1/2 hour.

title: peach delight
directions: In bottom of pie plate, put part of blended dry ingredients with margarine cut into it.
Add peaches, then add the rest of dry mixture.
Bake at
375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy lasagne casserole(doris kmiec, brenham, tx)
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until ground beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cook until thickened. Drain noodles.
Combine cream cheese and evaporated milk in warm saucepan until smooth.
Stir in noodles and garlic salt.
Pour into 9-inch square baking dish.
Spread meat mixture over.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream fan rolls
directions: In a bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar; let stand for 5 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the sour cream, eggs, butter, salt and remaining sugar.
Stir in baking powder, yeast mixture and 4 cups of flour until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: wonderful steak marinade
directions: Marinate the steaks 1 hour on each side.
Recipe is for 2 1/2 pounds of steak, about 5 servings.

title: wonderful chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Meanwhile, cut up chicken into 1/2 to 1-inch pieces.
Saute in pan.
When partially cooked, add chopped broccoli and cover.
Steam cook for 8 minutes.
Drain liquid.
Sprinkle cheese chunks on top. Cover and cook over very low heat until cheese is melted.
When rice is cooked and all liquid is absorbed, add sour cream.
Mix well.
Add rice/sour cream to the chicken/broccoli/cheese.
Mix well and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and serve.
Delicious!

title: coconut cream pie(made in blender)
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: my mom's buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour and Crisco.
Add buttermilk until mixture becomes easy to roll.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Knead mixture.
Roll out dough.
Crisco the bottom of the pan/glass Pyrex dish.
Cut out round-shaped biscuits.
Place in pan/dish.
Brush top of biscuits with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients and spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in tightly covered jar.
Put 1 or 2 teaspoons in cup of boiling water.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy skillet.
Cook slowly.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add salt and peanuts.
Cook to hard crack stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and soda (mixture will be bubbly).
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until foamy, about 25 seconds.
Serve immediately.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add one egg at a time.
Add flour and cream together.
Mix together with all other ingredients and bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Combine pancake mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add milk, oleo and egg.
Beat these ingredients and fold in apples. Bake on greased griddle.
Combine the 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and top pancakes when done.

title: corn flake squares
directions: Bring karo and sugar to boil.
Stir in peanut butter and then stir in corn flakes.
Press in 9x13 in. pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: hurry up brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a 1-quart saucepan over low heat. Stir to prevent sticking and to blend.
Add sugar, flour, egg, salt and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until well blended.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cut in squares while still warm.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in skillet.
Mix pork and beans and add drained kidney beans.
Stir in ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between additions.
Add vanilla, then alternately, the dry ingredients and milk.
Stir in prunes and nuts.
Bake in an 11 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add buttermilk, milk and beaten eggs, mixing well.
Add melted butter.
For each pancake, spoon about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle or iron skillet.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges are brown.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients, tossing together lightly with a fork.
Gradually blend the salad dressing and seasonings into whipped cream.
Pour over salad ingredients in bowl; fork-toss to mix lightly but thoroughly.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Serve on chilled, crisp greens, or use to fill center of a tomato.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of crock-pot; sprinkle Good Seasons Italian dressing mix over chicken. Add celery soup (do not add water), spreading soup over chicken. Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Half hour before serving, add 8 ounces fat-free sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles. Leftovers may need another can of soup added.

title: squash delight
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in pan or baking dish. Spread rice around in pan.
Spread squash over rice.
Add onions over squash.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix water with the soup and pour over the mixture and cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Arrange in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs; spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares for serving.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil, the oil, water and chocolate.
Take off heat and add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add flour and salt. Beat together well the eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Add to other mixture.
Grease pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger in heavy kettle.
Add vegetables, seasonings and the rice and water.
Simmer slowly for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl; mix well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diabetic spice cookies
directions: Mix water, shortening, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and boil together, cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad(number of servings: 4)
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, celery, grapes and parsley. Combine the next 7 ingredients; mix well. Pour over chicken mixture and toss. Chill for at least 1 hour. Before serving, sprinkle with sliced almonds.

title: all in one casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Tater Tots; put into casserole. Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: grits casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (until firm).
Good idea to mix night before.
Great breakfast dish served with fruit!

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking pan.
Mix butter, honey, mustard and curry powder together.
Pour over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Baste frequently.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Beat water, milk, salt, oil, sugar and eggs until mixed; add yeast.
Stir until it is dissolved.
Add flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down and make rolls.
Take 1/3 of dough at a time, roll out; put on butter, cinnamon and brown sugar with chocolate chips, cherries, pecans or raisins.
Roll like jelly roll; cut slices and put on cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot, stirring occasionally, until red hots are melted.
Squeeze juice of other 1/2 orange and float other half.
Serve hot.

title: baked seasoned salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 400 or 450°.
Arrange a single layer of salmon in a shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour half of the sauce mixture over the fish or salmon.
Bake for 20 minutes, basting with the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika and chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: catalina stew
directions: Brown meat in dressing.
Add water and vegetables.
Simmer slowly in electric skillet or Dutch oven.

title: mrs. batch's pie(original recipe from the white house, 1965)
directions: Mix together lemon juice, Eagle Brand milk, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: chocolate pie(2 pies)
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.

title: johnny mazetti
directions: Saute hamburg, add celery, onion and green pepper (chopped or ground).
Simmer to cook.
Add soup, paste, sauce, water, garlic, olives and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked noodles and mix well.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (if frozen 2 hours).
Makes two large dishes.

title: arroz con pollo(a classic central american dish)
directions: Put chicken, carrot, 1 cup each onions and celery, 1/2 teaspoon comino, 1/2 teaspoon oregano, 1 clove garlic, salt and pepper and water to cover.
Poach gently until tender, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.
Let simmer, do not boil.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and place in an 8-inch square baking dish.
Make 3 wells in the dry ingredients.
In the largest well, put the oil or shortening.
In the next, put the vinegar and in the third, put the vanilla.
Pour the water over all the mixture and thoroughly mix with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring mixture to a boil and simmer until it thickens.
This freezes very well.

title: sauteed zucchini and mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and zucchini in vinegar in a nonstick skillet until just crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining
ingredients and remove from heat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat liquid Butter Buds in a nonstick skillet and brown chicken, onion and garlic.
Add all other ingredients, except mushrooms.
Bring to boil, then cover and simmer about 30 minutes. Add mushrooms and cook 10 minutes more.
Remove chicken from pan; boil down sauce until slightly thickened.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight jar. Put in 2 to 3 teaspoons in cup of boiling water.

title: sticky buns
directions: In bowl, mix together sugar, milk, margarine, cinnamon and pudding.
Cut 1 loaf of bread into 12 pieces.
Place in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 pudding mixture over top of bread. Cut remaining loaf into 12 pieces.
Place on top of other bread. Pour remaining pudding mixture over bread.
Let rise until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While still hot, invert onto aluminum foil.
Clean pan and return rolls in foil to it.

title: pitas
directions: Cook ground beef and drain well.
Add seasoning mix, water, tomatoes and green chilies and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut bread rounds in half.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 250° for 10 minutes, or until warm.
Fill each pocket half full with meat mixture and top with lettuce and cheese.
Yield:
10 sandwiches.

title: pineapple-cheese spread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, pineapple, green pepper, chives, soy sauce, pecans and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours; serve cold.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, boil, drain and mash potatoes.
Beat and add remaining ingredients until fluffy.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan, sprayed with cooking spray.

title: punch
directions: Make ice cubes with one bottle of Sprite.
Make ice cubes with 1 bottle punch.
Mix three cans of water with frozen orange juice and also make into ice cubes.

title: easy shrimp casserole
directions: Combine rice, shrimp, onion, pepper and dressing in a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Top casserole with raw bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: septic tank cleaner
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pour into the toilet bowl and flush.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar until forms soft ball. Add butter and peanut butter and beat until hardens around edges of pan. Pour into buttered pan to cool.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Cook on medium heat until thick.

title: harvard beets
directions: Note:
Taste before adding salt; most canned beets already have salt added.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in Eagle Brand, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or a 2-quart container. Cover and freeze.

title: super steak and kidney pie
directions: Place steak, onion and kidneys in pan and cover with water. Bring to boil and skim off liquid.
Simmer about 1 hour, having added bay leaf, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain, saving liquid. Place meat and onion mix into 9-inch pan.
Cover with mushroom halves; thicken liquid with flour and add a dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Place pie crust holder in center of dish.
Cover with flaky pastry.
Brush with egg whites, beaten, and bake in oven until pastry browns.

title: fruit fizz
directions: Mix well
and
freeze
until slushy the Hawaiian Punch, pineapple juice and lemonade.
Put into punch bowl; add Sprite or ginger ale.
Mix and serve.
Makes 20 servings.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice, in small saucepan. Set pineapple aside.
To saucepan, add sugar, flour, eggs, orange juice, lemon juice and oil.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat and let cool.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Steam shredded cabbage; drain and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix or shake in jar remaining ingredients; pour over cabbage.

title: garlic herb spread
directions: In a small bowl mix all ingredients until well blended. Excellent for
garlic
bread
or to season fish or chicken for grilling.
Store in covered container.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Make into small balls, about the size of a large marble.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit tea
directions: Pour 3 cups boiling water over the two tea bags.
Let set for a few minutes.
Pour sugar and hot tea together into one gallon tea jug.
Stir until sugar melts.
Add orange juice and lemon aid. Fill the gallon jug with water.

title: throw together soup
directions: In large pot, or crock-pot, add beef, potatoes, carrots, onions and water; simmer 3 hours on stove or overnight (6 to 8 hours) in crock-pot on low.
Add seasonings, noodles and sauce. Cook 1 more hour on stove or 3 to 4 more hours in crock-pot, stirring occasionally.

title: no bake cheesecake squares
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in crumbs and sugar. Press firmly on bottom of 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix in sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Chill 4 hours.
Cut into squares.
Serve plain or with fruit on top.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: kringle sticks
directions: Cut margarine into flour as for pie crust.
Add cream cheese; mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: hot rolls
directions: Make up like biscuit dough. Put in the refrigerator 1 hour or overnight to cool. Pinch off what you want to roll out. Put a little oil in pan. Cut out as biscuits. Flip over in oil. Let rise 1 hour in a warm place until doubled in size. Cook in 450° oven until brown.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour drained pineapple into dish, spreading evenly over bottom.
Add blueberries; spread evenly.
Add 3/4 cup sugar over this mixture (sprinkle).
Sprinkle box of cake mix over the mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Top with chopped nuts.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take spoon, cut down through mixture several times so juice can come to top.
Cook for an additional 20 minutes or until crunchy on top.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend 24 hours before use.

title: creamy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Stir well to blend.
Pour over chicken.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 12 servings.

title: rum balls
directions: In large bowl, combine crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Add milk and rum.
Mix well.
Chill 4 hours.
Dip palms in sugar.
Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Re-chill mixture if it becomes too soft. Cover and store in refrigerator.
If desired, re-roll in sugar again before serving.

title: funnel cake batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat oil in pan until hot. Pour batter through a funnel making designs by holding finger partially over funnel hole.
Cook until light brown on both sides. Drain and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: cheese balls
directions: Place cheese in a small bowl; let stand at room temperature until smooth.
Add onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, scraping sides and bottom of bowl.
Cover and let chill 8 hours.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients until thick, stirring constantly. When thick, add lemon juice.
Pour over 10 quarts of peeled, sliced apples.
Pack into jars.
Cold pack for 30 minutes.
Seal until ready to use.
One quart makes 1 pie.

title: rotini pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water. Cut up vegetables and mix with pasta.
Pour dressings and salad pepper juice over pasta a little at a time.
Taste and add liquids until you like the taste.
Remember that as this salad marinates it will get stronger.
Sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine jalapeno peppers, garlic, tomato paste, sugar, vinegar, alum and spices in blender.
Process until smooth. Combine with chopped vegetables in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Yield:
3 pints.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salt and onion; add chicken, rice, broth, soup and celery.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, eggs and sour milk.
Add flour and other dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then add hot water.
Add bananas. Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 325° to 350° oven until golden brown.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole dish. Break the 6 or 7 pieces of bread on top and pour melted margarine over this.
Bake at 350° until toasted or about 15 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix juices, water and sugar well and freeze in 2 gallon size Ziploc bags.
Remove from freezer and let thaw until slushy.
Add 1 bottle Sprite or ginger ale to each bag of juice in punch bowl. Makes 30 servings.

title: no-fail custard pie
directions: Beat eggs just to blend; add sugar.
Scald milk; add milk, vanilla and salt to egg mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 475° for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 425° for 10 minutes. It will be jiggly in the middle but sets when cool.
Very good, smooth custard.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Sift and mix all ingredients.
Serve by using 1/2 cup of mix and 1/2 cup hot water.

title: broccoli, chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Mix with other ingredients but use only 1/2 can cheese soup.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with rest of Cheddar cheese soup.
Crumble Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Cook at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: crab casserole
directions: Check crab meat for pieces of shell.
Prepare white sauce per package instructions, using half and half in place of milk.
As soon as white sauce thickens, mix in remaining ingredients.
Spread in 10 x 10-inch or 10 x 12-inch or similar size buttered casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes, then turn on broiler until casserole is lightly brown on top.

title: broccoli casserole(microwave)
directions: In microwave,
cook frozen broccoli 6 to 7 minutes on High, then drain.
On stove, heat remaining ingredients in saucepan for 1 minute on medium.
Add to drained broccoli.

title: steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
In a large skillet, brown meat in oil, on high heat.
Add onions.
Saute until crisp.
Blend soup, liquid from mushrooms and garlic salt.
Pour over steak.
Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until steak is tender.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.

title: garam masala(indian spice mix)
directions: In 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, combine and roast in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
In blender, place roasted spices.
Cover tightly; blend until fine.
Cool and store in covered container.

title: trifle
directions: Slice pound cake (1/4-inch thick) and line bottom of large rectangular pan (9 x 13) with pound cake. Make Jell-O (as directed) and pour while warm over pound cake. Spoon crushed pineapple over Jell-O. Make pudding (as directed) and pour over pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over top, covering all. Refrigerate. Add strawberries just before serving. Best made day before needed.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Spread mustard on slice of ham.
Lay slice of cheese on top of mustard.
Roll jelly roll style.
Cut into 3rds.
Put toothpick in each one to hold it together.
Serve on pretty party tray.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet.
Drain well.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread soup over ground beef.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Take out and put about 1/4 cup grated cheese on top.
Return to oven long enough to melt the cheese.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: Cut 6 tortillas into 1/2-inch wide strips; set aside.
Cut remaining into triangles; fry until crisp.
Set aside.
Saute onion in oil.
Add all, except cheese and paprika.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add tortilla strips and cheese; simmer 10 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika and serve with reserved chips.

title: sunshine slush
directions: Mix all together in blender, adding ice cubes one at a time. Serve immediately.
Great for breakfast.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix condensed milk with Cool Whip, then add chocolate milk. Put in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together. Combine the orange juice, rind, shortening and enough water to make 3/4 cup juice.
Add the beaten egg.
Pour mixture into dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen well.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.

title: laura lee's apple crisp
directions: Wash, pare, quarter and core apples.
Cut each quarter lengthwise into 3 or 4 slices.
Put sliced apples in bottom of a buttered baking dish.
Add water.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix with dressing packets.
Line greased baking dish with 1/3 of crumbs, then layer of chicken, then can of cream of chicken soup diluted with one can broth.
Put another layer of crumbs, a layer of chicken, then can of cream of mushroom soup diluted with one can of broth.
Cover with layer of crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and spicy barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add chicken.
Brown over medium-high heat.
Place, skin side up, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "quickie" fruit cake
directions: Disregard instructions on cake package.
Spray a Bundt pan with Pam and dust lightly with flour.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° until inserted toothpick comes out clean, approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream, if desired.

title: spicy tomato aspic
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Simmer together 15 minutes, tomato juice, salt, sugar, cayenne pepper, celery salt, bay leaf, onion and celery leaves.
Strain.
Add softened gelatin and lemon juice, stirring until dissolved.
Cool; add celery, black olives and onion.
Chill until firm.

title: brownies
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: potato helper
directions: Layer cooked potatoes in the bottom of a casserole dish, then a layer of ground beef and then a layer of cheese.
Repeat layering until you run out of ingredients.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Melt butter and mix in flour until smooth.
Add eggs and milk.
Layer macaroni and cheese in casserole dish.
Pour liquid mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Do not overcook.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In medium bowl, combine thawed strawberries, eggs and oil.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Pour into pans. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Contains about 195 calories per 1/2-inch slice.

title: potato wedges
directions: Place cut potatoes on broiler pan.
Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Broil for 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and turn into a towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll towel and cake into a roll together.
Let cool completely or refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add milk, salt and baking powder.
Stir in flour.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Combine butter, flour and nuts.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix milk and instant pudding.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate!

title: garden cheddar soup
directions: In stockpot, combine carrots, zucchini, tomatoes, celery, mushrooms, onion, garlic, beef broth and V-8 juice.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Stir in basil, red wine, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add cheese just before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken wings in large roasting pan.
Wash chicken wings and cut into two pieces.
Add to sauce. Marinate in refrigerator, turning several times.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Turn again before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then at 450° for 15 minutes.
Place under broiler a few minutes until brown and crispy.

title: swedish meatballs in sour cream sauce
directions: Mix together beef, bread crumbs, egg, milk, onion and seasonings.
Form into small balls.
Brown meat in oleo.
Add garlic, beef extract and flour that has been blended in the bouillon.
Cook over low heat until sauce is thick.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serve with hot buttered noodles.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Cream sugar, shortening and salt.
Add boiling water.
Add a little flour to cool.
Add egg mixture and a little flour.
Add water, yeast and rest of flour. Roll and put in icebox.
Remove 1 1/2 to 2 hours before cooking.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Mix and boil until soft ball forms in cold water. Before removing from stove, add 3 tablespoons butter. Remove from stove and let cool. Do not stir until cold.
Beat.

title: el chepo dip
directions: Mix all together in bowl or saucepan and mash beans to desired consistency.
If too thick, add some of reserved juice.

title: apple crisp cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Add salt, cinnamon, walnuts, baking soda, flour and vanilla.
Fold in apples.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes. Needs no frosting.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon. Cut in the butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Stir milk and oil in to beaten eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together, then add egg mixture and remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour into well-greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: taco filling
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions. Drain. Add other ingredients and simmer over low heat until most of the liquid is absorbed. Easily increased for more than 1 pound.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Put in dish. Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb and blueberry jam
directions: Cook rhubarb until soft. Add sugar and blueberry pie filling. Stir and put into jars.
Keeps well frozen.

title: mama's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and cook in uncooked pastry shell.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Pour milk over oats and let stand while creaming sugar and shortening.
Add eggs to these four ingredients and stir in flour, cinnamon and raisins and drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased and floured baking tin.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Yields about 5 dozen cookies.

title: taffy apple pie
directions: Mix caramel pieces with flour; add apple pieces, caramel topping and lemon juice. Put into pie shell and sprinkle pecan pieces on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° approximately 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: m&m cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in M&M's with a spoon.
Drop by the spoonful onto a baking sheet.
Bake about 9 minutes at 350° or until light brown.

title: chicken in honey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine honey, mustard and lemon juice. Butter bottom of 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Add chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with honey mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 30 minutes more.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, salt and sugar together.
Add Crisco and cut into dry mix then add the milk. Roll out dough and cut into biscuits.
Bake at 425 degrees until golden brown.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes. Place in a saucepan with 1/4 cup butter. Heat over medium until melted and smooth, stirring often. Place vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish. Pour cheese mixture over and mix well. Melt remaining butter. Stir in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve at once. Makes 4 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well with a spoon.
Combine dry ingredients and add gradually to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in greased square pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage primavera
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender; set aside.
Brown sliced sausage and drain.
Combine sausage, vegetables and cream. Simmer 2 minutes.
Add cheese and serve over cooked fettucine. Serves 6.

title: upside-down supper
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix ham, beans, corn, cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon over hot meat mixture, spreading batter evenly to edge of casserole. Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Invert each onto plate.
Makes 4 servings.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients well with mixer.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Spread 1/2 cake batter into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of brown sugar mixture and swirl with knife.
Spread rest of batter, sprinkle with rest of brown sugar, and swirl again.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla with enough milk to make a smooth glaze.
Spread on cake.

title: italian macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown beef with celery; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
In large bowl, combine cooked macaroni, eggs, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt; toss lightly.
Place mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press evenly in bottom of pan.
Pour meat mixture over macaroni; cover with foil.

title: grandma celia's pink apples
directions: Core, pare and cut 6 apples in halves, crosswise.
Boil 1 cup sugar with 1 1/2 cups water and 1/4 cup cinnamon hearts for 5 minutes.
Add apple halves and simmer until just tender.
Put apples and pink syrup in a Pyrex dish.
Serve around a roast or use as a dessert with whipped cream.
Yields 2 halves per person.

title: potato surprise
directions: In a large skillet, combine the potatoes, ham, onion and green pepper in the oil over moderately high heat. Cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour beaten eggs over the mixture; continue to stir until eggs are set. Serve hot.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Wash berries and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine sugar and flour; add water, small amounts at a time.
Stir in lemon juice.
Mix well and pour over berries.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place crust on top, slitting in 3 to 4 places.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt candy bars and marshmallows in milk in a double boiler; cool.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into cooled mixture. Pour into crust and chill.

title: greek-style pasta salad
directions: In a medium bowl, whisk together oil, lemon juice, oregano, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix in the tomatoes, Feta cheese and parsley and allow to marinate.
Add to cooled pasta and toss gently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients together (sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon).
Beat eggs with fork.
Add vanilla and mix together with grated zucchini. Add zucchini mixture to dry ingredients, alternating with oil. Blend in nuts (optional).
Lightly grease and flour two bread pans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: three cheese chicken lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, pimento, milk and basil. Lay 1/2 the noodles in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with half each the sauce, cottage cheese, chicken and American and Parmesan cheeses. Repeat layers except for the last 2 cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheeses.
Bake a few minutes more.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Mix all together and chill overnight.
Add pimento for color, if desired.

title: eclair cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil; remove from heat and stir until margarine is melted.
Whisk in flour.
Whisk in eggs, one at a time; blend very well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam); bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas pie
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple, sugar, cornstarch together and cook until thick. Stir in dry jello and let cool. Add bananas and nuts. Pour into pie shells and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: bean delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: tuna layered salad
directions: Layer in 3-quart serving bowl: lettuce, macaroni, cucumber, tomatoes, tuna, green peas and Cheddar cheese.
Spread salad dressing or mayonnaise over salad, sealing to edge of bowl. Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss to serve. Yield: 8 servings.
Preparation time: 20 minutes plus refrigerating.

title: upside-down apple pie
directions: Arrange nuts, flat sides up, in butter in deep 9-inch pie pan. Pat brown sugar over nuts.
Roll out 1/2 of pastry 1/8-inch thick and line pie pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon into pastry; cover with top crust.
Seal edges well and cut a few slashes in top crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes, then carefully turn out on serving plate.

title: buns
directions: Scald milk.
Heat to boiling point.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Dissolve yeast and water.
When milk mixture is cool, add yeast.
Mix well and add enough flour to make soft, not sticky, dough.
Put in greased bowl and grease top of dough. Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Make into rolls, coffee cakes, buns, etc.
Let rise until double and bake at 375°.

title: quick vegetables and beef
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, heat oil.
Add broccoli and cook until tender-crisp.
Add soup, Worcestershire sauce and rice. Heat thoroughly.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate chocolate crepes
directions: Sift flour and chocolate powder.
Mix with milk until batter is smooth.
Add sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, eggs and butter; blend well.
Make very thin crepes with batter; allow to cool.

title: beef stew with limas
directions: Melt butter in hot Dutch oven.
Saute onion until golden.
Add chuck and brown lightly.
Now add tomatoes, cinnamon stick, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours until meat is fork-tender.
Skim off fat.
Refrigerate stew, covered.

title: rawpy pie (nova scotia)
directions: Boil chicken until well done.
Add coarsely chopped onions. Grate potatoes into white cloth over a bowl, catching all liquid. Discard this juice," but save the starch portion and add back to potatoes.
Separate chicken from broth and remove bones and skin.

title: corn pone
directions: Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and sausage, then add Bisquick.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot stuff
directions: Cook everything together with just enough water to cover. Bring to a boil on high.
Reduce heat to a steady simmer.
Cook until tender.
Good with cornbread.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and sugar and let set for 2 minutes. Stir.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Mix 1/3 cup water, olive oil, salt and flour.
Add to first group of ingredients.
Mix well.
Knead. Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Grease well one large pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: southern pie
directions: Combine cereal and water.
Let stand until water is absorbed.

title: beef hash
directions: Thicken 2 cups beef broth by mixing well flour and 1/2 cup cold broth, or lukewarm (not hot); flour will lump, stir well. Pour in broth when it boils.
Add chopped onions.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Add beef.
If gravy is too thick, add more broth.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour in baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except grated cheese.
Grease pan or skillet.
Pour half the mixture into skillet and sprinkle on cheese. Do not stir.
Cover with remaining mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Put drained Veg-All in a greased casserole dish.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise, celery and onions, then spread over Veg-All.
Melt oleo and mix with crackers.
Sprinkle on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until thread spins. Add the peanuts and then stir continuously after the peanuts are added. Cook until it turns a brownish gold. Take from fire. Add butter, salt and soda. Pour onto buttered board and cool.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch baking dish and combine the first 4 ingredients and 1 cup cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk. Bake, covered, for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Turn the heat off. Add peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
Pour into greased dish.
Cool and cut into 1 or 2-inch squares.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream oleo and powdered sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and store in refrigerator overnight.
The next morning, roll small dabs (size of walnuts) and place on greased cookie sheets for 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Roll in powdered sugar and store in airtight container.

title: potato-carrot foil bake
directions: Cut off 2 large sheets of foil.
Lay them like a cross.
Onto foil slice potatoes, carrots and onion.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and margarine.
Fold foil to seal pouch securely.
Grill until done, 55 to 60 minutes.
Open pouch and sprinkle cheese over vegetables.
Close pouch; return to grill until cheese melts, about 1 minute.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a microwave-safe dish, brown meat with water*, stirring occasionally. Drain and set aside.

title: raisin loaf cake(diabetic)
directions: Cover raisins with water.
Cook until water is absorbed.
Add applesauce, eggs, liquid sweetener and oil; mix well.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, or until cake tests done.
Yields 16 servings.

title: norwegian cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and toss with salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
In a saucepan, heat sugar, vinegar, mustard and celery seed.
Cook until the sugar dissolves, about 10 minutes. Cool completely.
Add to the cabbage along with remaining vegetables; toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 week before serving.
Keeps for 4 to 6 weeks in the refrigerator.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: tea balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts, then add flour and mold into small balls.
With a teaspoon, press an indentation in top of each ball (for frosting after baking).
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and add frosting.

title: classic beef stroganoff
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon flour with salt.
Dredge meat in mixture. Heat skillet and add 2 tablespoons butter.
When heated, add sirloin strips and brown quickly, flipping meat to turn all sides. Add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes until onion is barely tender.
Remove meat and mushrooms.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to pan drippings.
When melted, blend 3 tablespoons flour. Add tomato paste slowly.
Pour cold meat.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Return meat and mushrooms to skillet and stir in sour cream and sherry.
Heat briefly.
Keep warm over hot water.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add oil, water, eggs and pumpkin to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 3 medium loaf pans, well greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake in 3 large 9-inch layers at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: busy day fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter, heating through, not browning.
Add ground beef, plus 3 teaspoons salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Spread into 2 quart baking dish.
Spread 3 cups cabbage; cover with meat mixture.
Top with 3 cups cabbage.
Spoon over top, 10 1/2 ounce can of condensed tomato soup.
Bake covered 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: potato cake
directions: Combine soft oleo, sugar, mashed potatoes and melted chocolate.
Add eggs.
Combine flour and soda; add to other mixture and add milk.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool and ice.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Place tomato quarters, juice, salt and pepper in small pan. Bring to a boil.
Simmer until tomatoes begin to soften.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sweetener, bread and margarine.
Serve. Equals 1/2 #A limited veggies, lunch bread and 1/6 fat allowance.

title: orange slice roll
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into 3 logs. Slice when chilled.

title: 5 flavors pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy; add eggs.
Mix flour and baking powder and add to mixture alternately with milk. Stir in extracts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice across grain into 2x1/4 in. strips. Brown steak in oil in a skillet over medium-high heat 4-6 minutes. Add beef broth and next four ingredients. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Combine cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce; stirring well. Add to beef mixture and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add tomato wedges and toss gently. Serve over rice.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; press in a long pan.
Melt chocolate chips in the top of a double boiler.
When all chips are melted in a smooth mixture, pour over top of candy.
Let cool 30 minutes before cutting into bars.

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Mix Cool Whip, egg and lemon cake mix together by hand. (Batter is very stiff.)
Roll cookie dough into a log shape and coat lightly with 10x sugar.
Pinch off small pieces of cookie dough (approximately quarter size) and drop in 10x sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: "kalops" swedish beef stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour; set aside.
In Dutch oven, melt butter over medium heat until golden brown.
Add meat and brown well. Sprinkle with any leftover flour and salt, allspice, bay leaves and 1 1/2 cups water.
Stir to loosen pan drippings.
Cover; simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally until meat is almost tender.
Add carrots and onions and more water, if necessary, to cover and simmer until meat and vegetables are tender.
Discard bay leaves.
Serve with mashed potatoes and pickled beets.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together. Then add to egg mixture.
Fold in carrots, nuts, raisins and flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick coconut cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat pudding and milk on low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in half of the whipped topping and 1/2 to 3/4 cup of coconut.
Pour into crust.
Spread with remaining whipped topping; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini mexicana
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes.
Place zucchini mixture in an 8-inch square baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 10 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy whipped cream
directions: Whip and chill for 1 hour.

title: salad dressing for slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat smooth.
Use as needed. This will keep in refrigerator several weeks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of stuffing mix and spice packet on bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix the soups and sour cream together in a bowl, then put broken up chicken on top of stuffing mix, then soup mixture on top of that, then add the rest of the stuffing mix and season pack on top.
Pour over the broth and melted butter.
Bake for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: on-call salad
directions: In a blender container or food processor bowl, combine garbanzo beans, mayonnaise or salad dressing and Green Goddess salad dressing.
Cover and blend until mixture is smooth.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of the mixture over each lahvosh cracker. Sprinkle shredded lettuce, shredded Cheddar cheese and sliced almonds over each cracker.
Layer lahvosh, 3 in a stack, to form 4 stacks.
Cover the salads with clear plastic wrap; refrigerate up to 4 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings; set aside.
Mix flour, corn meal, salt, sugar and egg together.
Add milk to the thickness or thinness to suit you, just so it sticks to onions. Drop into hot oil in deep fryer or saucepan until golden brown.

title: soda cracker bars
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Put soda crackers (salt side up) in pan.
Heat butter or margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Boil hard for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400° until crackers float.
Cool for just a second.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread when melted.
Top with chopped nuts.
Cut when warm.

title: cheese-spinach souffle roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray or butter a 15 x 12-inch jelly roll pan.
Line the pan with heavy wax paper and spray again.
In a large skillet, melt the butter.
Using a whisk, blend in the flour and pepper.
Gradually stir in the cream and cook until thickened.
Beat in the cheeses.
Gradually add the egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Beat the egg whites and 1 teaspoon of salt until foamy.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of cream of tartar and continue beating until stiff.
Carefully fold into the cheese sauce, one-third at a time.
Pour into the prepared pan.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until the center, when touched, feels firm.
Turn the sheet of souffle out on a sheet of aluminum foil.

title: era's shipwreck cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread in the pan the chopped pecans and coconut.
Mix the cake according to directions and spread on top of nuts and coconut.

title: butter pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt into a mixing bowl.
Cut butter into the flour with a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle on the ice water a little at a time, blending it quickly into the dough by gathering up the mixture, working it lightly with your fingers, then squeezing it together.
(Work fast as the mixture must stay cold.)

title: moussaka
directions: Lightly coat eggplant slices with flour.
Brown on both sides and set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat, then stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Simmer 1 or 2 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Melt the butter; stir in the brown sugar.
Refrigerate until cool.
Add the sour cream and vanilla.
Chill; serve with fruit.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and peppers; bring to a rolling boil. Cook 7 minutes.
Add Certo and stir.
Take off heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Add a few drops of food coloring; pour into jars and seal.
This is good with beans, meats, etc.
It can also be used as a snack.
Spread Ritz crackers with cream cheese and top crackers with Pepper Jelly.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Blend in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer graham crackers (do not crush); then add pudding mixture.
Repeat until you've made 3 layers, finishing up with crackers on top.

title: walnut stuffed chicken
directions: Pour croutettes stuffing mix into large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add to stuffing mix, tossing gently.
Stir lightly while adding hot water.
Gently stir in walnuts.

title: salad pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and let stand overnight in brine made with 1/2 cup salt to 3 quarts water.
Slice thin or chop fine the onions.
Mix sugar, spices, flour and vinegar.
Add cucumbers, onions and pimentos.
Cook 10 minutes.
Pack in jars while hot and seal at once.

title: chicken ring with mushroom sauce
directions: Cut up chicken; combine ingredients in order given and mix well.
If stock is used in place of milk, use less salt.
Pack mixture in two generous sized buttered ring molds and bake in slow oven (325°) for 45 to 60 minutes.
Allow chicken rings to stand for 10 minutes or longer in a warm place (this insures easy removal), then turn onto two large platters and fill centers with mushroom sauce.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Drain juice from beets and add water if necessary to make 1 cup.
Heat everything (except beets and eggs) to boiling.
Pour hot liquid over beets and cover.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Remove beets and place eggs in beet juice.
Place beets on top of the eggs.
If necessary, add enough water to cover eggs completely with beet juice.
Cover.
Refrigerate 48 hours.
Slice eggs lengthwise to serve.
Great for a picnic.

title: meatball stroganoff
directions: Mix beef, onion, egg, bread, salt and pepper; shape into 16 meatballs.
Brown in skillet (use shortening if needed).
Pour off drippings.
Add soup and water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring now and then.
Blend in sour cream.
Heat.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: In spring-form pan, fill bottom and sides with open ladyfingers.
Fill sides first, then go across bottom.

title: great-great aunt clara's broccoli supreme
directions: In mixing bowl, combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
In small pan, melt butter, add stuffing mix, tossing to coat.
Stir 3/4 cup mix into vegetables.
Put in ungreased 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining mix.
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Blend soy sauce, chicken broth, sugar and cornstarch in small bowl; set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons of
Crisco oil in skillet. Add beef and cook over medium heat until browned.
Remove beef and drippings; set aside.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Cook carrots until tender.
Add onions, mushrooms and rest of ingredients as desired (as many as can).
Stir-fry until onions are tender-crisp.
Stir in soy sauce mixture; cover and cook for 3 minutes.
Add beef; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with enough clam juice to make creamy.
Drain remaining juice from clams and stir clams into cream cheese, then stir in sour cream.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown pork (cut into cubes) in vegetable oil.
Add diced onions and celery.
Cover with water.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add Chop Suey vegetables and mushrooms. Add a little water for juice. Add 3 tbsp. LaChoy Sauce, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
To thicken, add a little corn starch with water.

title: quick franks & potatoes
directions: Split each frankfurter lengthwise and arrange in baking dish. Spoon 1 tbsp tomato sauce into each pocket.
Spoon mashed potatoes between frankfurters.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Place pie in preheated 450° oven.
Bake for 45 minutes (do not peek). To test, a silver knife inserted should be come out clean.
Cool.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix 3/4 cup water, milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Heat.
Let cool to lukewarm, then add beaten eggs.
Add yeast, then enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Grease top of dough.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Let rise about 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Knead well.
Roll out and cut.
Brush with butter and fold over.
Put in warm place and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° or 375° until brown.
Makes 5 dozen rolls.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Place contents of vegetable-seasoning packet and 2 tablespoons of the margarine in a large bowl.
Add hot water (I use more water, probably 2 1/2 cups, because I like moist dressing); stir to partially melt margarine.
Add stuffing crumbs; stir to moisten. Let stand until water is absorbed.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in an iron skillet or 9 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
If you use a glass dish, lower oven to 325°.
I use a tablespoon or so of pimento to add color.

title: giant old fashion oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beating

until well blended. Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt, gradually add to butter mixture. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts. Drop by 1/4 cup on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350°, 15-17 minutes until edges begin to brown. Let stand 3 minutes before removing. Makes 2 dozen really big cookies. Can be made smaller if desired.

title: rice casserole
directions: Fry sausage and break up in small pieces; drain.
Heat 4 1/2 cups water.
Add rice and soup; boil for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vegetables and sausage; mix well.
Put in baking dish; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dedy's mayo muffs
directions: Combine ingredients and mix just until moistened. Fill greased muffin tins. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 6 muffins.

title: chili parmesan chicken
directions: Mix cheese and chili powder in pie plate.
Add chicken; turn to evenly coat on all sides.
Place chicken on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and peppers in a large pan.
Drain fat. Stir in soup, salsa, water and olives.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare cornmeal mixes according to package. Put 1/2 in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then layer hot meat mixture real carefully.
Add remaining cornmeal on top.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven; top with grated cheese and halved cherry tomatoes.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Put in pie crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: french beef casserole
directions: Don't brown meat.
Put all ingredients in a covered dish. Bake in a 325° oven for 3 to 4
hours.
Makes its own gravy. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: First put in pressure cooker for 35 minutes; then let pressure cooker cool.
Take off lid, put on stove and let it come to a boil; then add 3 boiled eggs in it, 2 big cans biscuits or make own dough.
Let it cook 10 minutes, until done.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.

title: big mama's homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve shortening in hot water.
Make sure it is cooled a little.
Add sugar, salt, egg and yeast in lukewarm water.
Spoon in flour, a little at a time, and let rise overnight.
Roll out in the morning and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: noodle soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, water and noodles.
Add vegetables and cook 3 to 5 minutes until tender.
Add beaten egg.
Stir quickly. Looks like egg drop soup.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Wash the potatoes. Bake until done. Cool, peel and dice into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Chop the onions.
Mix through potatoes. Melt Cheez Whiz (microwave).
Pour (into) over the potatoes and mix through. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Let stand about 5 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream	margarine
and
Crisco.
Gradually
add
sugar beating well.
Add	eggs
one
at a time, beating between each addition.
Beat
until
you
can't	feel any sugar on spatula. Add flavoring.	Fold
in milk and flour that has been sifted 3 times. (Sift, measure.
Add baking powder and salt.) Put into a large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: party oyster crackers
directions: Pour mixture over oyster crackers.
Mix well.
Pour into shallow pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: sweet pickles made over
directions: Slice pickles 1/4-inch.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over pickles; leave overnight.
Bring vinegar, water and sugar to a boil.
Add celery seeds.
Pour over pickles.
Place in refrigerator 4 to 5 days before serving.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon container.
Finish filling with water to make 1 gallon.
Kool-Aid color is color of punch.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm (seasoned) or Stove Top stuffing mix.
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine and pour over the stuffing.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans and mix with first 5 ingredients. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Top with can of onion rings and heat another 5 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
Add well beaten egg yolks; cook until thickened. Remove from heat, add vanilla and coconut.
Cool.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: california veggies
directions: About a peck of dandelion leaves will be required for a pint when cooked.
Look each over carefully and wash well in several waters; lay them in cold water for twenty minutes.
Put over to cook in an abundance of boiling water; put in a tablespoonful of salt and cook from thirty to forty minutes.
They will require a longer time if the leaves are not tender.
When done, put in a colander; drain and press out all the water.
Return to the stove in a saucepan; season with a little pepper and a teaspoonful of butter.
Cut through with a sharp knife and mix thoroughly.
Put in a hot dish and garnish, if liked, with slices of cold hard-boiled eggs.
Serve with vinegar.
Some prefer to boil a small piece of fat salt pork, well washed, with the dandelions, putting it in when the water is changed.
Dandelions make very nice greens and are considered very wholesome, but can rarely be obtained outside of rural districts.
They certainly should be as marketable as spinach.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix together coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla. Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture gradually. Stir in chips. Bake at 375°.

title: spaghetti leglio e'olio
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil over low to medium heat, about 10 minutes.
Do not brown.
Cover and keep hot.
Add salt to boiling water and cook noodles until tender.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup water.
Stir reserved water into garlic mixture.
Pour over spaghetti and toss.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: painless pudding
directions: Crumble fig bars.
Add chopped nuts and moisten with Muscatel wine.
Chill.
Top with vanilla ice cream.

title: fiesta chili
directions: Melt fat in deep heavy pan; add chopped onions and diced jalapenos and cook over low heat until done, but not browned.
Add ground beef and cook until browned, about 10 minutes.
Drain liquid from beans into small bowl and save.
Add beans, soup, chili powder and salt to beef in pan.
Stir well.
Cover pan and let chili cook slowly over low heat for about 30 minutes.
If chili gets too dry, add desired amount of bean liquid.
Can be made ahead of time and reheated.
It even tastes better the next day.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased muffin pan or cups lined with paper.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes. So simple and yet so delicious!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 3 quart oblong baking dish combine soup, milk, thyme and pepper.
Stir in vegetable and chicken.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to bubble.
Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into 1/4's and arrange biscuits over mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cherry pie mix, pineapple and juice in pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Pat down.
Pour melted oleo over coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab or shrimp wedges
directions: Combine all ingredients, except seafood and muffins.
Gently stir in crabmeat or shrimp.
Spread mixture on split muffins and place on cookie sheet to freeze.
When frozen, cut each muffin into 6 wedges.
Bag and freeze until needed.
When ready to serve, take out amount needed and place on cookie sheet.
Broil until slightly bubbly and browned.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple ham crescents
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving juice.
Reserve 2 spears for sauces, chop and set aside.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Wrap ham and cheese around pineapple.
Place at widest part of crescent and roll up.
Place on baking sheet .
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
In saucepan, boil reserved juice with mustard until thickened, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in chopped pineapple.
Serve with crescents.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Combine meat, onion, sugar and chili sauce and saute in butter until meat changes color.
Add tomatoes and beans and simmer for 15 minutes.
Place meat mixture in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread cornbread batter on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: hot dog cheese rolls
directions: Combine bologna and cheese cubes with green onions, boiled eggs and olives.
Toss mixture with salad dressing and chili sauce; mix well.
Spread into hot dog buns; wrap in foil tightly. Bake 10 minutes at 400° or until cheese begins to melt.
Nice for after church snacks.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan bring sugar and milk to a boil and boil for 3 minutes. Then add peanut butter and mix well. Add marshmallow and mix well. Pour into an 8 inch square pan and chill until set.

title: favorite pecan pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pastry shell; bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Beat eggs until light and lemon colored; add sugar and corn syrup, beating until fluffy.
Add butter, salt and vanilla; stir well.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until center is firm.
Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten whole eggs. Add vanilla, vinegar and salt.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Start cooking at 300°.
Raise heat in 10 minutes to 350°.
It takes about 45 minutes in all to cook.
Makes 2 pies.

title: jello salad
