directions: Dissolve the circus peanuts and jello in the hot water.
When cool, add the pineapple and Cool Whip.

title: basic pudding or pie filling
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in a small amount of milk until blended.
Beat in egg yolks, then add rest of milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat (stir constantly until thick). Then add vanilla.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Heat soup slowly; do not boil.
Add gelatine and salt, then set aside.
Mix with Miracle Whip and cream cheese.
Add celery, onion and soup.
Then add shrimp.
Pour into quart mold and let stand in refrigerator at least 8 to 12 hours.
Very good on Triscuit crackers.

title: caramel dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with mixer.
Serve with sliced apples, that have been brushed with lemon juice to prevent browning.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all and put in greased 9X13 pan.
Top with topping.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add oil and meat to the pan. Spread the meat around the pan and begin to break it up. Combine brown sugar and steak seasoning. Add sugar and spice mixture to the skillet and combine. When the meat has browned, add onion and red peppers to the skillet. Reduce heat to medium and cook onions, peppers, red wine vinegar and Worcestershire
sauce with meat for 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce and paste to pan. Stir to combine. Reduce heat and simmer Sloppy Joe mixture
5 minutes longer. Using a large spoon or ice cream scoop, pile sloppy meat onto toasted, buttered bun bottoms and cover with bun tops. Garnish with sliced tomatoes and/or pickles.

title: easter sunday pork sausage ring
directions: Beat eggs; add the rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly. Grease a 6-cup ring mold.
Press meat mixture into mold.
Cover. Chill overnight in the refrigerator.
Next morning, unmold onto a foil covered broiler pan.
Poke a few holes in foil to allow grease to drain away while baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Scramble enough eggs for your guests; place ring on a serving platter and put scrambled eggs in the center.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Absolutely delicious!
I have to make two for our family.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs and blend well. Add flour, vanilla and 7-Up.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: chinese noodle casserole
directions: Mix together and bake.

title: dutch apple hot bread
directions: Add milk, sugar, butter and salt to scalded milk. Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast cake in lukewarm water.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine first mixture.
Add flour to make very stiff batter.
Cover batter and let set in warm
place to rise, about 25 minutes.
Work down and then spread in greased baking pan to a depth of 3/4 to 1-inch.
Brush with butter and let rise again. Peel apples and slice.
Arrange slices on dough, pressing slightly. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake in a moderate oven (350° to 375°) about 30 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients as you would a tossed salad.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serves 6 to 8.
Recipe can easily be halved. Especially good with a vegetable soup or your favorite pot of beans.

title: neil's hearty italian soup
directions: Saute sausage, onions and garlic; drain, if necessary.
Add beef broth, tomatoes, wine, sugar and herbs.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add pasta; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 to 6 minutes longer or until vegetables and pasta are tender.
Sprinkle with pepper and parsley.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in medium skillet.
Cook until brown and drain well.
Line the bottom of a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforations to seal. Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.

title: marshmallow peach pie
directions: In double boiler, heat marshmallows and milk until melted. Dice peaches and pour sugar over the top of them.
Stir and let stand until juicy.
When marshmallow mixture is cool and a little thick, fold in the peaches and whipped cream.
Pour into baked, cooled pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Using large kettle, boil first four ingredients until thread stage (238°).
Add butter and peanuts.
Stir; cook until golden brown (300°).
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Mixture will bubble up.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased cookie sheet. When cool, break into pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream in butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add bananas.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, pepper, cauliflower, onion, radishes and peas in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar.
Spread over salad to seal moisture in.
Spread cheese and bacon pieces on top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss well before serving.

title: cinnamon fingers
directions: Roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Combine the corn meal, flour, celery, onion and eggs. Add milk and mix to make batter.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine in each of two iron skillets. Add half the batter to each and bake until done. Break up bread in a large bowl.
Add 1 stick melted margarine, soups, sage, chicken and broth and black pepper.
Pour into crock-pot and cook 45 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup

title: hungarian nut rolls
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar together.
Add butter and margarine and mix like for pie dough.
Add egg yolks to cooled milk.	Make well in flour mixture and add milk mixture and yeast.
Blend together with hands (do not over knead).
Cover and place in refrigerator for few hours or overnight if desired.
Make into 1/2 pound balls (will make 6).

title: salmon patties
directions: Put drained salmon in bowl and remove skin as desired.
Add sour cream, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Crush corn flakes and add to mix until it holds shape (about 2 1/2 cups).
Flatten into patties and place in more crushed corn flakes.
Fry until golden brown.

title: pinwheels
directions: Spray 8 to 9-inch square pan with no-stick cooking spray. Spread on bottom and sides of pan with paper towel.
Mix gelatin and water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart microwavable bowl; microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes, stir to dissolve completely.
Count or measure marshmallows.
Add the marshmallows; microwave 1 minute or until marshmallows are puffed and almost melted.
Stir mixture slowly until marshmallows are completely melted and mixture is smooth. (Cream layer will float to top.)
Pour into prepared pan. Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set.
Loosen edges with knife. Starting at one edge, roll up tightly.
With seam side down, cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 pieces.

title: velvet shrimp
directions: Preheat cooking oil to 375°.
Mix flour and Old Bay seasoning in a Ziploc bag.
Rinse shrimp; place in Ziploc bag; shake evenly to coat shrimp.
Carefully place shrimp in hot cooking oil for 3 to 4 minutes or until the shrimp float on surface of oil.
Drain shrimp on paper towels and serve with Cocktail Sauce.

title: vegetables mornay
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package until barely tender. Melt 3 tablespoons of butter.
Blend in flour but do not brown. Add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add seasonings and cheese, stirring until cheese melts. Place drained vegetables in greased 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Cover with sauce.
Toss bread in remaining butter and scatter on top.
Bake in 450° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: garden stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Cut in half lengthwise and cook in boiling salted water 5 minutes; drain.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender but not brown.
Add limas, corn and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Season pepper; fill with vegetable mixture.
Combine bread crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle over stuffed peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy bake chocolate cake
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hungarian beef goulash
directions: In Dutch oven (8-quart size), brown beef shanks in hot oil until browned on all sides.
Remove meat and bones to plate.
In remaining drippings, cook onion until tender.
Stir in paprika. Cook 1 minute.
Return beef and bones to Dutch oven.
Add celery, carrots, tomatoes with their liquid, salt and 5 cups water to boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls out on a flat cookie sheet and bake at 350° for only 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: tiffany's poppy seed cake (bread)
directions: Mix together well; pour in greased and floured tins.
You also can use a Bundt pan to bake this in.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Mix together and put into an 8 x 8-inch pan (well-greased). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let brownies cool 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and remove from pan.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Sift
together	three times the flour, cornstarch, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.	Cream butter, Crisco and sugar well. Add
eggs
one
at	a time, beating well.
Add milk and flour mixture
to
creamed
sugar
and Crisco, beginning with flour
and ending with flour.	Add vanilla and coconut.
Stir. Beat with electric
mixer
for
5 minutes.
Cook at 325° in a 9-inch tube pan
for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done when tested by inserting and removing a toothpick that doesn't have dough on it.

title: chicken shells
directions: Cook large macaroni shells, then cool.
Mix broken pieces of chicken with mayonnaise and onion.
Mix.
Fill shells.
Place in baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup with water; pour over shells. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Combine sugar, flour, and pecans; set aside.
Mix melted butter, eggs, and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture.
Fill mini muffin pans (makes 2 dozen).
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix sugar and butter in bowl.
Stir in eggs until well blended. Add bananas, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts just until moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake about 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool about 5 to 10 minutes.
Loosen sides, then remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water and Coke or 7-Up and cool to jelly point, then add pineapple and marshmallows.
Congeal mixture.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost cookies when cool with cream cheese frosting.

title: beef roll ups
directions: Prepare stuffing as per directed on package.
Cut steak into 6 pieces (6 x 4-inches).
Place 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each piece of steak.
Starting at narrow end roll up, tuck ends in and fasten with toothpick or cord and tie together.
In skillet with shortening, brown on each side.
Pour off excess fat; cover with soup and water.
Put cover on and cook over low heat 1 hour or until done.
Turn occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: challah bread
directions: Early in the day or a day ahead:
In bowl, combine sugar, salt, yeast and 1 cup flour.
In saucepan, heat oil and 3/4 cup water until very warm (125°).
With mixer at low speed, beat liquid into dry ingredients.
Beat at medium for 2 minutes. Reserve 1 egg yolk.
To mixture in bowl, add egg white, 2 eggs and 1 cup flour; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups flour.
On floured surface, knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes, working in about 1/4 cup flour.

title: low-fat french fries
directions: Peel and slice potatoes for French fries.
Spray large cookie sheet with low-fat cooking spray.
Place potatoes on cookie sheet. Spray potatoes with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Turn potatoes and bake until light brown, about 5 more minutes.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cream cheese, salt, almond extract, vanilla and egg yolk; blend well.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Refrigerate dough at least 2 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll out on floured surface,
using 1/3 of dough at a time, to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes. Leave cookies plain or brush with egg white (slightly beaten) and sprinkle with colored sugar before cooking.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen, depending on how big and thick cookies are.

title: baked nuts
directions: Toast nuts at 300° on baking sheet for about 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Beat egg whites and fold in sugar and dash of salt. Beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread nuts in dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: tomato pie
directions: Put sliced tomatoes into baked pie shell. Mix cheese, mayonnaise and basil. Pour over tomatoes. Bake at 450° until cheese is melted.

title: karen's pizza casserole
directions: Salt and cook noodles and drain.
Fry sausage, then take out of casing and saute onions.
Add everything, except cheese.
Put half of it in casserole and then place cheese strips on top.
Put rest of mixture on top and then rest of cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful into hot broth. Cook 10 minutes with the lid off and 10 minutes with the lid on.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble raw ground meat loosely in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Spread undiluted soup over all.
Place frozen Tater Tots in rows across the whole pan.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops; lightly brown chops and drain on absorbent paper.
In a medium bowl, combine soup and milk. Reserve 1/2 cup for topping; add rice and 1/2 of dry soup mix. Pour mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 9-inch baking dish. Place pork chops on top.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chops and sprinkle with remaining dry soup mix.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: nuts and bolts party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in large roasting pan.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and celery salt.
Mix well. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool on paper toweling.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Pour rum over raisins, fruit cake mix and cherries.
Let set for 1 hour.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.	Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix creamed mixture with dry mixture, add fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll mixture into walnut size balls and bake at 325 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: hot spiced tomato juice
directions: Boil together all ingredients; strain and serve hot.
Garnish with sour cream dollops and parsley flakes (or fresh sprigs).
May be reheated.
Wonderful for cold weather.

title: easy sunday roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot the night before serving.
Add all ingredients.
Cook on low.
Next morning add potatoes and carrots. Ready to serve for lunch.

title: easy shrimp fried rice
directions: In oil brown onion well.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Add egg and stir constantly until cooked.
Add 5 cups cooked rice, Season-All, soy sauce, peas and carrots.
Mix together and cook over low fire about 5 minutes more, stirring constantly.

title: purple people cooler
directions: Put juice, milk and ice cream in blender and mix.
Pour into cups; top each with a seedless grape.

title: chicken-a-la hawaiian
directions: Combine barbecue sauce, orange juice, brown sugar, oil, flour and salt.
Mix well. Cook in skillet until mixture comes to a boil and thickens slightly.
Cut chicken in small pieces.
Put in baking dish.
Pour gravy mixture over chicken. Add pineapple, water chestnuts and ginger in sprinkling method over the top. Bake in a 300° oven 1/2 hour. Serve over rice with sprinkled almonds.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Place brisket on foil in a large baking pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and spoon over both sides of brisket.
Wrap in the foil and marinate overnight.
Sprinkle salt and spoon barbecue sauce over meat in the morning.
Wrap in foil and bake 4 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli according to package directions. Add food coloring during cooking time. Drain and then toss with a sufficient amount of oil so pasta doesn't stick together. Place all other ingredients over pasta and stir. Refrigerate and allow flavors to blend for a day or two. Will keep in refrigerator about 3 weeks.

title: morning muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Rub muffin tins with Crisco.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake in moderately hot oven (350° to 375°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins.
Serve with jelly or cream cheese.

title: swiss steak with rice
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Rub garlic into steak. Saute meat in oil with onion and green pepper.
Put remaining flour mixture in skillet, then add hot water to make gravy to pour over all.
Cover meat with onion, green pepper, rice and tomatoes. Cover tightly and simmer for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks until light and fluffy. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites and fold into the rest.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients and milk.
Pour batter into pan of melted margarine.
Add filling or peaches and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: parmesan potato sticks
directions: Cut potatoes into 6 or 8 wedges lengthwise.
Place shallow baking pan in a 425° oven with butter or margarine to melt.
Add potato sticks and bake for 20 to 30 minutes, turning occasionally. Sprinkle with salt and cheese.
Return to oven 2 to 3 minutes. (This is like French fry without the fry.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix smooth the sugar, vanilla, milk and cream cheese.
Fold in a carton of Cool Whip.
Break angel food cake and place in a large fruit bowl.
Pour mixture over cake and top with cherry pie filling.

title: busy day chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Cover bottom evenly with rice.
Arrange chicken pieces on rice.

title: cheddar nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix vigorously (by hand) for 30 seconds or until blended.
Spoon into a buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: recipe for a vital marriage
directions: Blend with much Understanding and lots of Forgiveness.
Bake continuously in the oven of Commitment and Trust.
Baste often and liberally with a Sense of Humor.
Serve with plenty of Communication in a Problem-Solving Atmosphere (especially good when shared with loving Family and Friends).

title: easiest ever biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients; mix and handle lightly.
Put out on floured surface and lightly roll.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place in greased pan.
Bake 13 minutes, then turn oven to broil. Broil 2 minutes or until browned.
Makes about 15 biscuits.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup crushed potato chips and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: homemade soap
directions: Cook when the moon is going full.
Heat water and then add grease.
Add lye and stir as needed.
Don't let it overflow.
Hold stir paddle up and it will thicken and string when ready.
Let fire die out naturally.
Set overnight or longer.
Skim off top as necessary.
Cut in bars.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Stir in brown sugar. Arrange pineapple in mixture.
Stir shortening to soften.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add juice, lemon peel and egg; mix until all flour is dampened.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes; invert on plate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with milk in a double boiler; set aside.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar and cocoa together; add to milk and eggs, then add vanilla and butter.
Cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Save the egg whites for meringue.

title: apricot squares
directions: Simmer apricots in 1 cup water for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon.
Stir into apricots; cook until bubbly, then 1 more minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Combine flour, oats and bran cereal.
Cut in margarine.
Set aside 1/2 crumb mix.
Stir in 3 tablespoons water into remaining crumbs.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top with apricot mixture, then reserved crumbs.
Press together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake by directions on package and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.
Also, make vanilla pudding by package directions. Start by crumbling 1/3 of cake in bottom of punch bowl or large salad bowl.
Spoon 1/3 of pudding over cake.
Spoon cherries and pineapple (use slotted spoon), leaving enough for 2 more layers. Spread layer of Cool Whip over this.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with Cool Whip on top.

title: grits angela(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a large box, mix melted Velveeta cheese, tomatoes and crumbled sausage. Stir. Add cooked grits to mixture. Stir. Beat egg. Slowly mix 2 to 3 teaspoons of hot grits mixture into beaten egg so egg warms slowly. Stir the egg-grits mixture into full pot of grits, tomatoes and sausage. (The egg step can be omitted, but it makes the final product fluffier.) Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Top with 1 1/2 to 2 cups freshly grated Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: potato candy
directions: First boil potato with skin on it.
Peel potato after its cooked.
Mash potato into sugar while hot.
Mix into stiff ball. Roll out onto wax paper.
Spread peanut butter on it.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Now slice into slices.

title: date, nut pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl; add Crisco, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix 2 to 3 minutes with electric mixer.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° to 350°, depending on oven, 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 6 dozen medium cookies.

title: barbecue cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage to base in 4 quarters, but do not cut all the way through.
Open cabbage and alternate layers of onion, pepper and tomato.
Add margarine.
Add bacon slices.
Wrap twice in heavy-duty foil, must be wrapped twice.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes in coals.

title: ruth's date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over mixture of dates, walnut pieces and soda and let stand.
Cream together sugar and lard or Crisco.
Add eggs.
Add water from dates.
Add flour and salt.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Do not frost.
Serves a lot of people.
Can be cut when cool into small loaf sizes.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and then aluminum foil.
Freeze.
Makes nice small gifts by adding brightly colored ribbon.

title: working girl's chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dilute soup with milk.
Place chicken in buttered casserole or baking dish and cover with diluted soup.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: basic sugar cookie dough
directions: Cream sugars, eggs, butter and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill for an hour or overnight.
Roll in balls or drop and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.

title: fantastic frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: fantastic fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift together sugar, flour and cocoa. In bowl, beat eggs; add flour mixture, butter, flavoring and pecans.
Pour in large baking dish.
Put in another pan with hot water.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not overbake.
They will firm up as they cool.
Will be like candy with crust.
Makes 36.

title: tamale dip
directions: Mix cheese, tamales and chili until cheese melts.
Stir often. Then add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over chips.

title: humus(chickpea dip)
directions: Drain liquid from chickpeas; reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Place chickpeas, lemon juice and reserved liquid in blender container; cover.
Puree, scraping sides of container frequently with spatula, until smooth.
Transfer chickpea mixture to medium size bowl; stir in sesame seed oil, garlic, snipped mint and salt.
Pour chickpea mixture into shallow serving bowl; make well in center.
Pour olive oil into well.
Garnish with mint leaves, olives and parsley. Sesame seed oil is called tahina in Middle East supermarket.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cook corn until soft in boiling salted water in a saucepan; drain thoroughly, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Melt butter with corn liquid in a saucepan.
Add flour and cook, stirring rapidly, until mixture is smooth and rolls away from the sides of the pan. Remove from heat.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in cooked corn.

title: magic cookie bar
directions: Pour melted butter or margarine in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle
graham
cracker
crumbs
even
over. Scatter chocolate morsels over nuts.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over chocolate pieces and nuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over.
Bake
at
for
25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool 15 minutes; cut into bars.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into loaf or into two loaves. Place in oven with small amount of water and in covered container. Roast at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as per package instructions and cool completely.
Chop tomato, cucumber and onion and add to the cooled macaroni and cheese.
Stir in Miracle Whip.
Chill.

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Combine water and vanilla.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Lightly coat both sides of 3 tortillas with cooking spray. Lightly brush each side with water mixture and sprinkle each side with about 3/4 teaspoon sugar mixture.
Place on a wire rack in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Repeat with remaining tortillas.
Contains 2.7 grams fat.

title: scrumptious sweet potato pie
directions: With an electric mixer, combine first 8 ingredients. Beat until well blended. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° for 40 minutes or until set. Cool on wire rack. Serves 8.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix in a large pan the sour cream, cream of chicken soup and mushrooms.
Cut up chicken in large pieces and spread over the mixture.
Then add prepared stuffing and spread over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot layered salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in cold water and then remaining ingredients.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: veggie hot dish
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch dish, place vegetables (frozen or thawed). Pour can of soup and rinse can out with small amount of milk. Cover veggies and soup with croutons and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Pour corn oil into fryer or skillet.
Clip the thermometer to edge.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Measure 1 1/2 tsp. corn oil into bowl; mix with fingers until combines.
Then add lukewarm water and evaporated milk; use finger tips to work liquid into dough until you can form sticky ball.
Pour dough out and knead for about 1 minutes with flour.
Cover dough with damp towel to rest for 15 minutes.
Divide dough evenly into 3 balls, cover dough with damp towel for another 20 minutes.
Take 1 ball and roll out with flour into circle.
Trim off rough edges, cut into 6 wedge shapes.
Roll out other balls. Heat oil to 380-390 degrees until light brown.
Remove from oil and place on paper towels.

title: jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water. Let cool. Drain all syrup off of crushed pineapple into measuring cup. Add enough cold water to make 1 cup and add to Jell-O. Add sour cream. Using electric mixer, blend on medium-low speed until all of sour cream is dissolved and mixture is smooth. Stir in crushed pineapple and cherries if you wish. Grease lightly 10 to 12-cup mold with mayonnaise. Pour mixture by cupfuls into mold. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased, floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After cake cools, drizzle with powdered sugar icing (optional).

title: peanut butter haystacks
directions: Melt peanut butter chips and chocolate chips in double boiler. Stir in peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper.
Let set until hard.

title: cranberry waldorf
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes and walnuts.
Fold in container of Cool Whip.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken, onions, parsley flakes, bouillon cubes, salt and pepper and 4 cups water in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Boil until chicken is done.
Remove chicken to cool.
You should have 3 to 4 cups of broth
left.
Add soups to broth.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and let simmer.
Cook egg noodles according to directions.
Cut chicken into cubes.
Add to soup.
Drain noodles and add to soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with toasted barbecue bread.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in Earthenware or china dish.
Combine salt, pepper, brown sugar, bay leaves and mixed spices with enough 1/2 cider vinegar and 1/2 water mixture to cover meat.
Heat to boiling and pour over meat.
Allow meat to cool.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 days, covered.
Turn occasionally.
Put meat in a roaster with a little spiced vinegar.
Roast at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is brown and tender.
Remove meat from pan.

title: hot and spicy chicken wings
directions: Follow directions on Shake 'n Bake box.
Double chicken pieces for wings.
Bake in oven until done.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Gently simmer chicken until tender (approximately 20 minutes). Remove chicken from the bone and cut up in small chunks.

title: betty's chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Just add 1/3 cup mixture and cup water to make chocolate drink.

title: sweet and juicy cheesesteak
directions: In large frying pan, cook onions and chip steak until done. Add sweet pepper strips including the juice.
Let the juice cook down a little, about 5 minutes.
Place 2 slices of cheese in roll and add steak mixture and serve.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage leaves that have been separated for 2 to 3 minutes.
Place meat, rice, salt, pepper and lemon juice in a bowl and mix well.
Stuff and roll cabbage leaves with meat mixture into small firm rolls.
Arrange the rolls in baking dish.
Place 2 cloves garlic between each layer.
Add water, tomatoes and tomato paste and cover and bake until done.

title: stuffed mushrooms 1
directions: Remove stems and toss mushrooms with 1 large clove garlic (minced).

Saute mushrooms and garlic in 3 tablespoons sweet butter or olive oil for parsley (minced), pepper to taste, 1/4 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1/3 cup fresh bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon fresh oregano leaves (minced) or 1 teaspoon dry leaves.
Stuff mushroom caps and place in buttered 8 x 11-inch gratin dish.
Add 1/2 cup dry white wine to pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Place under broiler for 1 minute or until tops are golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes; peel.
Add butter or hot mash with masher. After thoroughly mashing, pour into pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: turtle hot dogs
directions: Split hamburger rolls into halves and place under broiler until toasted.
Keep warm.
Heat beans in small saucepan or microwave until heated through.
Keep warm.
Split frankfurters into halves lengthwise.
Melt butter in small skillet.
Add frankfurters and cook until lightly browned.
Spread pickle relish on bottom halves of toasted rolls.
Top each with 2 frankfurter slices, forming X. Spoon on beans, then top with tops of rolls.
Push carrot sticks into olives, then insert carrots into rolls to form turtle head. Makes 4 servings.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut chicken into serving pieces. Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: sweet potato raisin patties
directions: Mash sweet potatoes. Beat in egg and salt. Add flour only if potatoes are wet.
Mix in raisins. Drop by tablespoon on heated greased frypan.
Brown slowly on both sides.

title: theresa's butterscotch cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugars until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda, butterscotch chips and oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain water from tuna; break up with fork.
Add chopped onion, celery and apple.
Sprinkle lemon juice over.
Add mayonnaise and stir up good.
Use as is or make a sandwich.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour over graham crackers, arranged on cookie sheet close together.
Place in oven and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: bagels
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 cup warm water in measuring cup, stirring with a fork until dissolved.
Combine 2 cups flour, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Add dissolved yeast and remaining cup of warm water.
Beat vigorously with a fork for two minutes. Gradually add enough of remaining flour, 1/4 cup at a time, to make a soft dough.
Turn out of bowl; knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes), adding a little flour.
Place dough back in clean, greased bowl; put in a warm place until doubled in size.

title: cheese macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all the ingredients in casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Top with Ritz crackers and bake at 350° until hot.

title: cherry coconut bars
directions: Mix together 1 cup flour, confectioners sugar and butter. This mixture will be very coarse.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine eggs, cherries, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Mix in flour, baking powder and sugar.
Spread onto baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: *Use all sauce, except 1 cup.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and then lower heat to 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until custard is set.

title: congealed blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in wine. Refrigerate until mixture thickens.
Fold in blueberries and oranges.
Spoon into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: lime-cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in water; cool.
Combine cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts; chill.
Mix Cool Whip and both chilled mixtures together.
Pour into an oiled 2-quart mold. Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler and add 1/2 square paraffin.
Roll peanut butter mixture into small balls and dip in chocolate mixture.
(Use a toothpick and swirl in chocolate.)

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Drain corn.
Layer rice and corn; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can of tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Layer onion and green pepper, then ground beef. Sprinkle with pepper and salt.
Pour over second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer.
Add strips of bacon, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: water rolls
directions: Work first 7 ingredients into a dough and add rest of flour. Place in refrigerator until ready to use.
Make rolls and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 450°.

title: p. b. and fudge ice cream pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey.
Stir mixture into softened ice cream.
Spoon half of ice cream mixture into pie crust.
Sprinkle with half of chopped cashews.
Drizzle 4 ounces fudge sauce over cashews.
Spoon remaining ice cream mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle with remaining cashews.
Drizzle 2 ounces fudge sauce over cashews.
Freeze overnight.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cucumbers and onions.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour this over the cucumbers and onions and toss.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: egg casserole
directions: Butter bread and cut crust off.
Cut into cubes and sprinkle with mustard and salt.
Add grated cheese.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Pile cornflakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is set.
Use 7 1/2 x 12-inch or 8 x 13-inch pan.

title: stove top chicken and noodles
directions: In large saucepan, mix soup, milk, cheese, pepper, chicken and noodles.
Over medium heat, heat through, stirring occasionally. Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and 2 sticks of butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together 2 sticks softened butter, powdered sugar and eggs.
Spread onto crust.

title: ham, potato and bean dinner
directions: The amounts you use will depend on how big your family is.

title: ham and cheese log
directions: Let cheese stand until soft.
Cut ham into small pieces. Cream the cheese and remaining ingredients and form into ball. Chill.

title: world's best sugar cookie
directions: Cream together sugar, powdered sugar and margarine.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls. Place on cookie sheet and press with glass bottom dipped in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 350° for 60 minutes in loaf pans.

title: super good salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add marshmallows and heat until dissolved.
Add softened cream cheese and heat well.
Cool slightly.
Fold in grated carrots, pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip and chill.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix eggs and oil together.
Add remaining ingredients and beat 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes four layers. Cook at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken ole
directions: Lightly grease bottom and sides of crock-pot.
In large bowl, mix together soups, sour cream, diced chilies and onion.
Arrange alternate layers of tortillas with chicken and mixture.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook on low another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Combine soup mix, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add cheese gradually, stirring constantly until all cheese melts.
Serve with French bread cubes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together mashed avocados with lemon juice.
Mix all ingredients and serve with tortilla chips.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Mix oatmeal and hot water and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add the oatmeal mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake the cake mix as directions say in an 11 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cooled cake will be first layer.
Second layer: Cream the sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup of Cool Whip together and spread on cake. Refrigerate until set.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together and chill.

title: pressure-cooked wild turkey
directions: Place prepared turkey in a pressure canner.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook until done, according to directions in your pressure canner booklet.
Remove turkey from canner and put in a large baking pan.
Broil very carefully until brown.
Rub with a stick of butter or margarine during broiling, if meat appears to be drying out.
Also, place foil over breast if it starts to burn. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mama's cold biscuit pudding(over 50 years old)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in the top of a double boiler; stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thick. Beat egg yolks and stir into hot mixture.
Cook 5 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
